title: barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Let cool and store in the refrigerator until ready to use.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: joan's bean dip
directions: Spread beans on bottom of 9 x 13-inch container or pan.
Then add remaining items in layers.
Sprinkle cheese on and top with olives, sliced.
Serve with taco chips.

title: deviled chicken breasts(serves 4)
directions: Toss chicken breasts and breadcrumbs in large Ziploc bag to coat.
Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Brown chicken on each side for 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Add wine, savory, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken and mushrooms with slotted spoon and place on serving plate.
Add lemon juice and honey mustard to skillet; stir well. Cook 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve sauce over chicken.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake rolls at 375° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dry dressing.
Spread over crescents. Add vegetables and top with cheese.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Combine other ingredients together, then add hamburger mixture.
Place in greased casserole and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Break up vermicelli in melted butter and brown.
Add consomme and water.
Add rice.
Heat until hot.
Cover and cook 45 minutes with lid on.
No peeking!
Add almonds, mushrooms and chives. Bake 45 minutes in casserole at 350°.
Serves 16; may be halved.

title: wylene's sherried beef
directions: Combine all ingredients. Simmer 3 to 5 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
This is very good served over Wylene's Wild Rice Baron.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Combine meat, milk and crumbs.
Form into balls.
Brown in hot fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meat balls and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian ricotta pie
directions: Mix all ingredients into a ball.
Roll dough between wax paper, making a crust for a 10 x 13 inch pan and leaving enough dough for lattice on top.
Line the dough on bottom and sides of pan. Pour in filling.
Make lattice for top.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean (as a custard pie).
Use a glass pan to make it easy to store.

title: custard pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually stir in scalded milk. Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife in center of custard comes out clean.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Brown
chicken	breasts.
Cook	noodles,
broccoli
and carrots separately.
In 13 x 9-inch
baking dish, mix noodles, broccoli and carrots.
Place chicken breasts
on
top.
In pan the chicken
was
browned
in, add soup and milk.
When warm, pour over casserole and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low heat, stirring.
Cool slightly; stir in powdered sugar and egg.
Beat to creamy and glossy.
Put in marshmallows and nuts to coat.
Put coconut on wax paper and roll mixture in it.
Shape into roll.
Make into two rolls.
Slice.
No bake.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix and Crisco oil until creamed.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add instant pudding mix and Seven-Up.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients.
In another bowl, stir together next 5 ingredients.
Stir flour mixture into carrot mixture. Add nuts and raisins.
Spoon into a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove.
Cool on wire rack.
Wrap and store overnight before serving.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: primavera salad
directions: Remove broccoli leaves and tough ends and discard.
Wash good and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Cook in boiling water, covered, for 1 minute.
Drain immediately and plunge in ice cold water to stop the cooking process.
Drain, pat dry and chill.
Cook pastry from package directions.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain again.
Combine pasta and Versatile Vinaigrette and toss to coat. Place in a large Ziploc bag and chill for 2 hours or overnight. Wash spinach and remove stems.
Combine spinach, pasta, broccoli, turkey and remaining ingredients; toss gently.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix in a clean bowl; let stand for 6 hours.
Add it and let stand for 3 hours; make sure the mixture bubbles up.

title: fried peach pie mix
directions: Remove seeds.
Chop peaches, peeling and all, with a food chopper until they are in very, very small pieces.
Boil sugar and vinegar until sugar is melted.
Add chopped peaches and cook until mixture is of spreading consistency.
Pour into clean, hot jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.
Use as filling for fried pies.

title: snack crackers
directions: Whisk together oil and dressing mix in a large bowl; pour over crackers, tossing to coat. Spread mixture on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, stirring after 7 minutes. Yields 6 cups.

title: rabbit salad
directions: Cut up the rabbit meat into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and chill about 1 hour in the refrigerator.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressing and cheese.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serve with freshly ground black pepper.

title: chinese spinach
directions: Heat oil, soy sauce, lime juice, sugar and pepper in large skillet.
Add garlic.
Stir-fry over medium high heat about 1 minute or until garlic is light brown.
Add onion; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add spinach, water chestnuts and pimiento.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until spinach is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick and easy pizza
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add
milk
and oil. Pat dough into bottom
on greased pizza pan.
Mix pizza sauce, water and seasonings.
Spread
over
dough,
then
sprinkle on onion, mushrooms (well
drained),
hamburger and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dump dessert
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan; spread can of pineapple.
Spread can of pie filling next.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly on top, then sprinkle brown sugar, then pecans.
Last, slice stick of butter and arrange over top of all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Boil together until well done. Next; add one stick of margarine and 1 bag of croutons. Add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning to taste. You need enough croutons to make it hold together. Roll into balls and bake until done.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Chop peppers.
Shred cheese.
Layer peppers and cheese in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour eggs over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve warm. The more jalapenos, the better.

title: candy quickies
directions: In double boiler, put Chinese noodles, butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Add peanut butter and butterscotch chips.
Blend. Stir in noodles.
Spoon on wax paper to cool.
Spread peanut butter between Ritz crackers and then dip in melted white chocolate.
Dip Ritz crackers or wafer thin crackers in mint flavored white chocolate.

title: mom's bar-b-q
directions: Brown ground beef and onions with celery. Salt to taste. Add rest of ingredients and simmer until it thickens.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken for an hour.
Drain water, but save.
Let chicken cool.
Add all other ingredients except noodles to chicken broth and boil again.
Remove chicken from bones and add meat to soup. Boil at least 1 hour; add noodles and serve.

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In a casserole, layer ingredients in order listed, topping with soup.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Make sauce of mayonnaise, soup, eggs, onion, cheese and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: connie's easy french bread
directions: Put yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water and mix.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and hot water.
Stir in the flour, one cup at a time, and mix after each cup.
After all the flour is added, let dough set for 15 minutes, then stir again and let set again for 15 minutes.
Do this 4 times (takes 1 hour).
Let dough set, covered, until it doubles.
Form into 1 loaf and put on floured baking sheet.
Brush the top with cold water and make 5 slashes diagonally in top of loaf with sharp knife.
Let loaf rise for 30 minutes and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate-dipped cinnamon crisps
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut each unbaked shell into 8 wedges. Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake for 4 to 7 minutes or until golden brown.
In small saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Place pan in warm water to keep chocolate soft.
Line baking sheets with waxed paper.
In plastic bag, combine sugar and cinnamon.
Gently shake a few wedges at a time.
Dip wide end of each wedge in melted chocolate.
Place on waxed paper and refrigerate until chocolate is set.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Place
soft tortillas, cut in quarters, over bottom and
sides of pan.
Mix browned hamburger, onion, soups, green
chilies and sauce.
Layer in pan with tortillas and cheese on top each.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until bubbly.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together (better if done by hand).
Roll dough into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press each ball with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out. Whip one egg white and spread over dough.
Sprinkle with sugar and chopped nuts.
Cut with pizza cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: moist and tasty meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Shape firmly into loaf.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, then glaze with catsup and continue baking approximately 15 more minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° in Bundt pan or until done.

title: apple crunch
directions: Preheat
oven to 375°.	Combine brown sugar, oats and 3 cups of	flour.	With
fingertips,
work
in
the shortening. Press half
the
mixture	into
bottom
of a well greased 10 x 15-inch roasting or baking pan.
Combine apples with remaining flour, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and the sugar; spread on top of the
oat mixture.
Add
and press down remaining oat mixture. Sprinkle with
remaining
cinnamon and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternate vanilla wafer crumbs and milk.
Fold in pecans and coconut.
Bake 2 hours in Bundt pan at 275°.
Cool completely before removing from Bundt pan.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients, reserving small amount of grated cheese, to sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: angel dessert
directions: Put bite size pieces of angel food cake into a 9 x 9-inch dish.
In a separate bowl, combine pudding and milk.
Add ice cream.
Beat until well blended, then spoon over cake. Refrigerate.

title: cranberry cooler
directions: In a 2-cup liquid measure or small pitcher, combine cranberry juice, nectar and orange juice and stir well.
Divide ice into each of two 10 ounce glasses.
Pour half of the cranberry mixture and half of the club soda (or seltzer) into each glass.
It makes 2 servings, about 3/4 cup each.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo until clear.
Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Mix broccoli with soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add to onion, celery and oleo.
Stir in rice.
Season and mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas ornament clay bake(dried in an oven)
directions: Tempera paint, a basic printing medium, can be purchased in a liquid form or a powdered form.
The dry tempera must be mixed with a liquid.
Mix powdered tempera directly with liquid starch or make paste using 1/4 cup water and 1 teaspoon dry wheat paste (wallpaper paste).
Then add 1/4 cup of liquid starch to achieve proper consistency.
Mix in powdered tempera for color.

title: oyster cracker delight
directions: Put all ingredients except crackers in a large container that will seal tightly.
Mix dry ingredients into oil, well.
Add oyster crackers; shake, then let set a few hours and shake again. Do not open for 24 hours.

title: piggie peach custard pie
directions: Slice the peaches on the bottom of an unbaked pie shell.
Mix well the sugar, eggs, flour and butter and pour slowly over peaches.
Bake 15 minutes at 425° or bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: raspberry jelly
directions: Put all together in large pan.
Let boil, stirring slightly, until skin forms on top.
Take off heat and skim off top layer of skin.
Throw away.
Put in jelly jars.
Put wax on top and put paper on top, then cover tightly.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on an 11 x 15-inch ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes until light brown. Cool.
Blend cream cheese with salad dressing.
Spread cream mixture on top of baked crust.
Sprinkle chopped vegetables on top of creamed mixture. Top with 2 cups of grated Cheddar cheese. Serve cold.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients, but optional bread crumbs.
Gently pat into
crab	cakes.	Roll cakes in bread crumbs if desired. Fry in cooking oil over medium heat until brown.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain all juice from the pineapple and cherries and heat until it bubbles around the edge of the pan.
Use this to mix the jello. Dissolve all jello, then add Coke.
Mix well and let stand in refrigerator until it starts to congeal.
Mix in cream cheese (cut into small cubes), pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 6 hours before serving.

title: mama's cucumber pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onions and peppers in large crock or pan.
Mix ice and salt;
pour over cucumbers.
Let set for 3 hours; drain and put in pot.
Pour remaining ingredients over cucumbers.
Bring to a boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: *Or use 1 cup butter Crisco in place of the butter and shortening.

title: pistachio fluff
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crush Ritz crackers into crumbs.
Melt butter.
Put on cracker crumbs spread in pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes, then cool.
Mix pudding, milk and softened ice cream together.
Pour onto crust.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pistachios and cherries on top.

title: refrigerated dill cucumbers
directions: Make a brine by combining water, vinegar and salt and bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Quarter cucumbers lengthwise and put in a large bowl with dill and peeled garlic cloves.
Pour cooled brine over cucumbers.
Cover bowl and weight contents down, if necessary, to keep cucumbers covered with brine.
Put bowl in refrigerator 4 days.
Put pickles and brine in jars.
Must keep refrigerated. Will keep several months.

title: frosia
directions: Wash and dry basil leaves.
Stack leaves and chop finely. Crack eggs into a bowl and beat with a fork.
Add the basil, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper and stir to mix.
Let set a few minutes and, if mixture appears dry, add 1 or 2 more eggs. Mixture needs to be consistency of heavy pancake batter.

title: praline sauce
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil; cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in pecans and vanilla.
Cool slightly; serve warm over slices of pie.
Yields 2 cups.

title: oatmeal crust
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Cut in other ingredients with a pastry blender, beginning with the butter.
Blend it until mixture resembles coarse crumbs, then stir in oats.
Sprinkle milk over mixture.
Stir lightly and form into ball.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Roll to form circle.
Fit into a 9-inch pan. Crimp around edges.
Prick sides and bottom if using for a cream pie.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
May also be used unbaked for custard or chess pies.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine margarine or shortening, peanut butter, egg and white sugar together.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Chill dough.
Make balls size of large walnuts.
Place 3-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet. Flatten and crisscross with a floured fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups hot water. When dissolved, add 3/4 cup cold water. Add strawberries and chill until set.
Mix pudding according to directions on box. Chill until set.
Layer cake, jello and pudding in a punch bowl or very large glass bowl. Finish with whipped cream on top.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup brown sugar and coconut. Put in an 8-inch round greased and floured cake pan or smaller. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of brown sugar and coconut over top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.
Frost while warm.

title: scallops and linguine
directions: Cook linguine to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain; rinse with hot water.
In large bowl, combine scallops, lemon juice and garlic.
Sprinkle with parsley, dill weed, salt and pepper; toss gently.
Cover; refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes to blend flavors.
In large saucepan, melt butter.
Drain scallops well; saute 3 to 4 minutes, coating well with butter.
Add cream, heating thoroughly, about 1 minute.
Over medium-high heat, add linguine to scallop mixture, tossing gently to distribute scallops and heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ham salad for sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salad is ready for sandwiches.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix everything well.
Put in a covered bowl overnight in refrigerator.
Mix with fruit before serving.
Chop all fruit and sprinkle with Fruit-Fresh.
Mix well in a large bowl.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling, then cool and let stand a few hours for flavors to blend.
Just before serving, reheat and strain out spices.

title: almonry biscuits
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and oats together.
Melt margarine and syrup over low heat.
Add baking soda and milk to melted mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: fudge mallow raisin candy
directions: Microwave chocolate and peanut butter in 2-quart bowl for 2 to 3 minutes, or until melted.
Stir after each minute.
Fold in marshmallows and raisins.
Pour into foil lined 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm.

title: mexican chili
directions: In large skillet, brown beef, onion,
green pepper and garlic.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain green limas and kidney beans.
Mix all ingredients; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(If mixed ahead of time, the flavor is better.)
Good for carry-in dinners in a slow cooker.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Combine all the dry ingredients; add oil, eggs and carrots. Mix on low speed until well blended; stir in pineapple and nuts. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans; cool completely on wire racks. Frost with cream cheese.

title: chicken dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients the night before serving.
Serve with cubed bread or crackers.

title: pizza quickie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Pat biscuits on cookie sheet until very thin.
Bake for 4 minutes.
Brown meats separately; drain grease.
Rinse and then chop vegetables.
Spread sauce over biscuits.
Top with desired toppings; meats first and then vegetables.
Sprinkle with both cheeses.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes until cheese is bubbly.
Substitute with slices of barbecue bread for French bread style pizza.

title: hamburger in a skillet
directions: Saute rice in margarine until golden brown.
Add meat, onion and celery and brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: peach smash
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender container and blend until well mixed and frosty.
Pour into chilled glasses.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs with pumpkin; mix all dry ingredients together. Mix with pumpkin and egg.
Bake in greased and lightly floured loaf pan for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Fill a salad bowl 1/2 full with the lettuce.
Make 1 layer each of the onions, green peppers, celery and peas. Spread the mayonnaise and cheese over top. Top with the bacon.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: artichoke delight
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until bubbly, about 45 minutes.

title: banana teething biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir until smooth.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in greased loaf pan.
Cool; remove from pan.
Cut into sticks.
Rebake at 150° until hard and crunchy.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes and reduce heat to 400° until pumpkin is set.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Prepare and bake brownie mix using package directions. Sprinkle marshmallows over hot brownies.
Combine chips and milk in saucepan.
Cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Drizzle over brownies.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: barbecued pork
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker; cover and cook on high 8 hours. Shred meat with fork. Mix into sauce and heat through. Serve on hamburger/sandwich buns with grated cheese and cole slaw on top.

title: flag dessert
directions: Slice 1 cup of the strawberries. Set aside.
Halve remaining strawberries and set aside.
Line bottom of 12 x 18-inch baking dish with cake slices. Top with 1 cup sliced
strawberries, 1 cup of the blueberries and all of the whipped topping.
Place strawberry halves and remaining 1/3 cup blueberries on whipped topping to make flag design.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil all ingredients, except Cheez Whiz and broccoli, until tender.
In another container, cook broccoli florets until tender. Add Cheez Whiz to soup mixture and then add broccoli.
Serve immediately.

title: pickled squash
directions: Place squash and onion in enamel pan, cover with water and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons salt.
Let stand one hour, stirring a few times.
Drain well and mix squash with remaining ingredients and bring to a good boil.

title: ham salad(made with bologna)
directions: Grind all ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Moisten with salad dressing.
One-half pound cheese (grated) may be added.

title: strawberry dream
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix jello according to directions on package, using 3 cups of water.
Pour this over cake pieces.
Add strawberries and pecans on top of this.
Mix instant pudding according to package directions using 3 cups of milk.
Pour over the strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: cracked wheat rolls
directions: Place 1 cup whole wheat kernels in blender.
Cover; blend on highest setting for 1 1/2 minutes or until kernels are coarsely ground.
Combine cracked wheat and 1 1/2 cups warm water; let stand 15 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Drain, pressing out excess liquid.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown meat with celery, bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Drain fat. Add all other ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over Fritos corn chips or rice.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Add onion, sauce, water and spices.
Cook rotini as directed while meat sauce simmers.
Drain pasta.
Place in baking dish.
Top with meat mixture.
Layer pepperoni on top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Blend well.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini.
Sprinkle with nuts and chips, after pouring batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
(No need for frosting; zucchini makes cake moist, too.)

title: carrot-potato combo
directions: Boil potatoes and carrots.
Cool; grate.
Combine soup, sour cream, butter, cheese, salt and pepper.
Combine with potatoes and carrots in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley. Cover; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: sweet pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie crust shells, with mixer.
Put in pie crust shells.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon or nutmeg. Bake at 425° for the first 15 minutes; reduce heat to 375° and bake 25 minutes more.
Total baking time is 40 minutes.
Yields two (9-inch) pies.

title: annie's shrimp fettuccini
directions: Add onions and celery to melted butter in a large heavy sauce pan.
Saut for 10 minutes until onion is clear.
Add flour and mix well.
Cook until thickened.
Add parsley and shrimp.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cream, cheese, and garlic.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook covered on low heat for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix in cooked and drained noodles.
Pour into a buttered 3 quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: jimmie's fried chicken
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet on medium.
Season fryer.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop egg on fryer.
Mix, coating every piece.
Place one at a time into flour, coating each piece.
Drop, skin side up, into medium hot oil.
Fry 3 minutes.
Turn and fry 3 more minutes. Cover with lid.
Check fryer and turn 3 or 4 times every 4 minutes.
Uncover and let chicken get golden brown and crispy.

title: bountiful black bean soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine beans with enough water to cover by 1-inch. Bring to boil over high heat. Boil 1 minute. Remove pan from heat. Cover tightly and let stand 1 hour (or soak beans overnight in large bowl with enough cold water to cover by 1-inch). Drain beans.

title: peach yogurt shake
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients, except peach slices and mint.
Cover and blend on medium speed until smooth.

title: easy white sauce
directions: Crumb together with pastry blender all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator indefinitely.
As needed, spoon out a little into hot liquids, peas or other vegetables.
Stir as it thickens. Saves on another dirty pan.

title: kool-aid dessert
directions: Mix the Clear Jell with enough water to make a smooth paste before adding to main amount of water.
Cook until clear.
Add 2 (3 ounce) packages of orange jello.
When cool, add fresh, frozen or canned fruit.

title: zucchini appetizer squares
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut in squares.
Enjoy!

title: pour pizza
directions: Lightly brown hamburg and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine flour, salt, pepper, oregano, eggs and milk, making a soft batter.
Grease a 9x13 pan and sprinkle lightly with cornmeal (or flour).

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and brown and white sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat very well.
Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add coconut.
Spread into 2 large (9 x 13-inch) well greased pans, about 1/2-inch deep.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cut in squares while still warm.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, noodles, vegetable soup, water, Worcestershire sauce, salt and oregano.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, stir and then bake 7 more minutes.

title: mock whipped cream frosting
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Cook milk and cornstarch together.
Cool.
Add cooked mixture to creamed mixture, beating constantly until light and fluffy.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Sprinkle chicken with paprika. In a large skillet, brown chicken in 2 teaspoons butter. Place the vegetables in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with chicken. Melt the remaining butter. Stir in the tarragon, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Pour over chicken and vegetables. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, until vegetables are tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix everything together and put in a 3-quart casserole dish. Cover top with bread crumbs and pour 1/2 of the margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
This recipe makes enough for 30 people.

title: dad's prime rib
directions: Rub garlic all over roast.
Generously salt and pepper roast. Roast in a 400° preheated oven for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 15 minutes per pound.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill 3 hours.
Roll into ball. Serve with crackers.

title: grandmother's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Add milk and soda mixture alternately with sifted flour and nutmeg.
Add vanilla.
Roll out not too thin; cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in 350° oven until just done, but not too brown.
May be iced or sprinkled with sugar, if desired.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt if Crisco is used instead of butter.

title: salsa
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator.

title: meat-shell potato pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings.
Press firmly into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; spoon off fat.
Frost with potatoes.
Top with remaining soup, cheese and bacon.
Bake 10 minutes more until done.
Makes one 9-inch meat pie.

title: nut kipferl
directions: Mix flour, sugar and walnuts.
Cut butter into fine particles. Add vanilla and work by hand to form a ball and dough holds together.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone; place in large casserole dish.
Mix chicken soup and 1/2 cup water.
Pour this over deboned chicken. Slice boiled eggs on top of this.
Melt butter.
Mix flour and milk; shake real well.
Pour this over the first mixture; be sure to cover good.
Pour 2 cups of broth over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn broiler on to brown the top.
Delicious.

title: fancy corn bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Beat eggs; add milk and melted butter.
Add corn, peppers, cheese and onion.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese straws
directions: Have butter soft.
Cream and add cheese, then add salt and red pepper.
Press through star cookie press.
Bake at 375° until barely crisp.

title: banana creme pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; set aside.
Scald milk in top of double boiler (water boiling in bottom pan) on low heat.
Add flour and sugar mixture.
Stirring occasionally, cook for 7 minutes.
Stir in two eggs (well beaten first) and vanilla; cook 3 minutes.
Let cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, bananas, soda, salt, flavoring and nuts.
Mix.
Pour into prepared loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or until done.

title: mexican rice
directions: Combine water, dry mustard and bouillon granules in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir in rice and chopped green peppers.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in chopped green chives.
Fluff with a fork before serving.
Yields 6 servings.
Contains 97 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: blue cheese log
directions: Bring cream cheese, Blue cheese and butter to room temperature.
Mix together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into a log on wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Before serving, cover with sliced almonds which have been toasted in oven with butter.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix with powdered sugar in bowl; set aside.
Melt peanut butter and margarine in medium saucepan.
Add to graham crackers and powdered sugar mixture.
Mix well and pat into the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set in fridge.

title: zucchini bread
directions: *You can use 3/4 cup brown sugar and 3/4 cup white sugar.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Salt can be added to taste.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Place pie crust upside down in a square baking dish or pan.
Pour peaches over pie crust.
Sprinkle cake mix over peaches.
Slice butter over cake min.
Bake in oven for 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: corn and asparagus bake
directions: Cook asparagus slightly less time than package directions. Drain corn, reserving liquid.
Stir flour into melted butter; blend well.
Stir milk and corn liquid gradually into flour mixture.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add cheese, egg, parsley, salt and celery salt; stir well until mixture thickens. Add almonds.
Remove from heat.
Layer corn, asparagus and sauce in a greased 3-quart baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix beaten egg, butter and Parmesan cheese with drained pasta. Pat down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cottage cheese.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; drain.
Add mushroom soup and rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and stir for a few minutes, topping with chow mein noodles.
Soy sauce may be also used on top.

title: better than potato salad
directions: Cook rice to package directions.
Transfer to bowl.
Cover and chill.
Add mayonnaise or salad dressing, celery, onion, mustard and salt to chilled rice.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.
Stir in remaining ingredients before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 generous servings.
A great alternative to potato salad for picnics or family reunions.

title: easy christmas fruit cake
directions: Empty cake mix into a large bowl.
Mix well with eggs, water and oil.
In another bowl, mix candied fruit, raisins and walnuts in 2/3 cup flour so they don't sink to bottom of cake.
Mix batter and fruit mixture together.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when inserted.
Remove from oven.
While cake is warm, drizzle with mixture of 1 cup of powdered sugar and a few tablespoons of warm water.
Decorate top with maraschino cherries, pieces of green fruit from fruit mixture and walnuts.

title: honey rose cheese cake
directions: Cream together the first six ingredients.
Sift flour, cinnamon and salt together.
Add alternately with part of the buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Add vinegar and soda to the last part of the buttermilk and mix well.
Add red food coloring to complete mixture and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: corn plus vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Grease glass dish.
Pour ingredients in (except 1/2 of the cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup cheese).
Mix well, then add remaining topping.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: hummus(chickpea spread)
directions: Start your food processor and then put in garlic.
As soon as garlic is minced, put in chickpeas, lemon juice, salt, tahini and cold water.
Blend until smooth.
Add more cold water if you want it thinner.
Empty contents into a shallow 6-inch wide bowl. Smooth contents.
Sprinkle with paprika and cumin, then drizzle oil over it.
Best served at room temperature.
Dip with pita bread.

title: hot salsa
directions: Blend peppers, onions, garlic, cumin and cilantro with a small amount of tomato juice from your can of tomatoes.
Blend in blender until your cilantro is well blended.
Put tomatoes in and blend for 10 to 20 seconds.
You don't want it real mushy.
Cook in a pot on top of stove on medium heat for 30 minutes.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese with salt, pepper, grated Parmesan cheese, parsley and spinach.
Cook lasagna and drain.
Spread tomato sauce on bottom of pan, layering alternating lasagna mixture and tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: lemon cheese squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until light brown.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and spread on cooled crust.
Mix last two ingredients as directed on pudding box. Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: corn flaked chicken
directions: Rinse off chicken and pat dry.
Melt butter; set aside to cool.
Crush the corn flakes with a rolling pin.
Blend together the butter and paprika.
Dip the chicken pieces into the butter mixture, then roll the pieces in the corn flakes, covering all sides.
Place the chicken on a cookie sheet and place in oven at 350°.
Cook for about 1 hour, or until crisp.

title: hillbilly
directions: Boil noodles until soft and set aside.
Brown meat with onion. Season.
Make a layer of 1/2 of the noodles in the bottom of a 2 quart greased casserole dish.
Place 1/2 of the meat on top.
Pour 1/2 of the corn over the meat.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of green pepper and a thin layer of cubed cheese over this.
Repeat the entire process.
Pour the tomato soup over all and top with more cheese.
Bake uncovered.
Serves 12.

title: ruth's potato salad
directions: Mix together in order.
Chill and serve.

title: black olive chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat oil in a large ovenproof skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken. Cook, turning occasionally, until browned, about 5 minutes per side. Add tomatoes, garlic, parsley, thyme, broth and lemon juice to skillet; stir well. Cover skillet. Place skillet in oven. Bake chicken for 20 minutes, basting occasionally with sauce. Add olives to skillet. Bake for 10 minutes longer or until juices run clear when meat is pierced with a knife. Sprinkle cayenne pepper over top just before serving.

title: pecan munchies
directions: Fold pecans in egg white mixture until well coated.
Place on slightly greased baking sheet at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave for 30 more minutes.

title: mondel bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until thick and creamy. In a separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients. Alternate dry ingredients with egg mixture. Add oil and mix well. Add nuts. Grease and flour a cookie sheet. Shape bread into two loaves and bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
Slice diagonally and put back into the oven to toast for 5-10 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Put in crock pot.
Pour barbecue sauce over chicken and cook in crock-pot overnight on low.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: pepper relish
directions: Soak ground vegetables overnight or at least for 4 hours.
Mix with 1/2 cup plain salt; drain well.
Combine and bring to boil the spices, water, sugar and vinegar.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: fruit topped cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, mix until blended; pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set; cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fruit. Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage soup micaele
directions: In a large kettle or dutch oven, saute carrots and celery in 1/4 c. (1/2 stick) butter until vegetables are softened.
Add leeks and cabbage and saute 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken stock, bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Stir in 10 ounces 7-Up.
Mix and bake at 350°.

title: turkey quiche
directions: Press leftover stuffing into a 9-inch pie plate, forming a crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: venison tenderloins
directions: Whip eggs and milk together.
Dip tenderloin in mixture and coat with corn flake crumbs.
Season with salt and pepper. Put in pan and bake
in
a 350° oven for 1 hour.
When the top and sides are nicely browned, turn over.
Serves 4 people.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add taco seasoning and water. Simmer 5 minutes.
Place in a dish in layers as follows: beans, cheese, hamburger, salsa, sour cream, tomatoes and onions.

title: peanut butter oat bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the butter, 1/4 cup peanut butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and vanilla; gradually add the oats. Press into a 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool on wire rack for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, for topping, melt chips and 1/3 cup peanut butter in microwave for 1 minute.
Stir until blended and spread over warm bars.
Cool completely and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before cutting.

title: ham loaf
directions: Pour over loaf.
Baste with sauce while cooking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak dried beans overnight. Rinse well. Cover with 2 qts. of water, more or less. Add onion, vinegar, and oil. Simmer 3 hours or longer. Add carrots and potatoes. Simmer until all is cooked, then add salt & pepper to taste. 20 minutes before serving, gently slip in eggs to poach. (1 egg per person.)

title: spinach bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9x13 pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes till golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate puffs(a macaroon-type cookie)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until blended.
Add salt and vanilla.
Fold in melted chocolate, coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet. Bake in slow oven (300°) for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and salt with cold water and ice cubes.
Let sit about 3 hours.
Do not use metal container.
Mix sugar, vinegar, turmeric and celery seed and simmer 30 minutes. Pour cold water off cucumbers and pack in jars; cover with hot liquid.
Process 10 minutes in hot water bath.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, soak the bread crumbs in cream and milk; mix meat.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In a large skillet brown and cook meatballs in oil. Combine beef consomme (1 can) and heavy cream to make sauce.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: parmesan chicken wings
directions: Dip chicken wings in butter then in combined dry ingredients. Put on foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes.
Yum!

title: thistle dip
directions: Puree undrained artichoke hearts in blender or processor until very smooth.
Transfer to bowl and blend in sour cream, garlic, onion salt and red pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour. Sprinkle with paprika and serve with crackers.

title: chow mein
directions: Saute first four ingredients in oil.
Remove from the saute pan.
Then brown the ground beef with 1 teaspoon salt and pepper. Drain off any fat.
Combine cornstarch with water.
Mix with soy sauce.
Add to meat and vegetables.
Cook and stir until thickened. Move mixture to the side of the pan.
Add boiling water and instant rice; add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cover and remove from heat; let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork; then serve.

title: yellow squash muffins
directions: Wash squash thoroughly; trim off ends.
Cut squash into one-inch slices.
Cook in small amount of boiling water for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Measure enough of the squash to equal two eggs and butter.
Stir well and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Add squash mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling three-fourths full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes with fork and wrap in foil.
Fill the crock pot with potatoes.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or high 2 1/2 to 4 hours.
Do not add water.
No oven to heat up and they stay hot.

title: texas style spanish rice
directions: In a skillet, saute onion and green pepper in oil for about 2 minutes.
Add rice and stir until coated with oil.
Add tomatoes, turmeric, cumin, salt, garlic powder and water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Add cilantro if desired.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: german chocolate sheet cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions substituting milk for water.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans in pan.
Pour cake mix over coconut and pecans.
Melt cream cheese and margarine together.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix well (until easy to pour).
Pour over cake mix.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sunspot banana gems
directions: Cream sugars and margarine.
Beat in egg, bananas, oil and yogurt.
Grate vegetable.
Stir in dry ingredients until all is moistened.
Add grated vegetable, raisins and nuts (optional).

title: one-pan tomato basil chicken
directions: In a large skillet, prepare Rice-A-Roni mix as package directs, except simmer 10 minutes. Stir in chicken, basil, broccoli and tomato. Cover and continue to simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle with cheese before serving, if desired. Serves 4.
Ready in 30 minutes.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Cook corned beef in oven at 300° until tender. Or cook in crock-pot overnight. Cut cabbage into thin wedges; cook with beef until done. Season to taste.

title: jiffy cobbler
directions: In a
small
pan, about 8 x 8-inches, put 1/2 box Jiffy cake mix
in
the
bottom.
Pour
pie
filling over the bottom layer. Over
this
layer put the rest of the cake mix.
Place butter on top
and
bake
at 350° until brown.
For a crunchy crust, mix cake with butter and add 1/4 cup pecans or walnuts for flavor.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Put sugar, milk, salt and shortening in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until shortening melts.
Remove and stir until lukewarm. Sprinkle in yeast and dissolve.
Add flour and baking powder.
Stir until smooth (about 30 strokes).
Let stand.

title: firecracker enchilada casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender; discard pan drippings.
Add chili powder, cumin and salt; stir well.
Cook meat mixture over low heat for 10 minutes.
Spoon meat mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer beans, tortillas and cheeses over meat mixture. Chop tomatoes and spread tomatoes and chiles over cheeses.
Pour soup over tomatoes.
Cover baking pan and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: four layer cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over chilled mixture.
Put remainder of Cool Whip on top of pudding topping and sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn in blender.
Stir in corn. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain grease.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add tomato paste.
Let simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Boil macaroni until tender.
Combine both ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix fruit with sugar.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Melt butter. Make batter with remaining ingredients.
Pour batter over butter, then pour fruit and juices over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: copper dollar salad
directions: Cover the carrots with water and cook 7 minutes ONLY!
Drain. While the carrots are cooking mix other ingredients together. Pour this over the drained carrots, tossing real good.
Put in refrigerator and this is good for 4 weeks.
The longer it is in the fridge the better it tastes.

title: rio grande pork roast
directions: Rub surfaces of roast with garlic pepper.
Place roast in a shallow pan and place in a preheated 350° oven; roast for 30 minutes.
To make basting sauce, combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl; stir to mix well.
Pour basting sauce over roast and continue to roast, basting occasionally, until meat thermometer inserted registers 155°, about 20 to 30 more minutes.
Remove roast from pan and let rest 10 minutes before slicing to serve.
Remove pan drippings to a small saucepan; add enough water to make one cup and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve sauce on side with roast.
Serves four to six well, with leftovers.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain, if necessary.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed except omit 1/4 cup of water and add 1/2 cup Eagle Brand milk to mix.
Pour 1/2 the batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Take out of oven and have ready the caramel mixture.
Melt caramels in 1/2 can Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over first 1/2 of cake in pan, sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over the caramel mixture.
Add remaining batter. Bake until done.
You may ice cake with chocolate icing.
This is a very rich cake.

title: raspberry buttermilk muffins
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles crumbs.
Add egg and buttermilk.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in berries.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until brown.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread.
Add all the other ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until browned.

title: pork chop mein
directions: Saute onions and celery in oil for 5 minutes.
Add pork, broth, soy sauce and molasses.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add bean sprouts. Stir in cornstarch blended with a little broth.
Cook until thickened.
Serve on chow mein noodles or rice.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes; drain.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Have ready:
onion, cheese and jalapenos.
Mix first 7 ingredients and set aside.

title: no bake fudgies
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, margarine, milk and salt.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, corn meal and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Bake in pie shells until done at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, cutting bacon into smaller pieces.
Pour into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monster cookies
directions: In a dishpan, combine ingredients in the order listed, adding one at a time.
Mix thoroughly between each addition.
Using a small ice cream scoop or tablespoon, place mound of dough on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool before removing from sheet.
This is great for parties because it serves 80.

title: grandma foland's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Bake at 475° for 9 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a loaf pan with cooking spray. In large bowl, beat oil and 1/3 cup sugar.
Add banana and chopped walnuts, mixing well.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Slowly add 1/3 cup sugar, beating until whites form peaks. Fold whites into batter.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 55 minutes.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Combine water and black-eyed peas in large saucepan.
Cook until almost tender, about one hour.
Add more water, if needed. Heat Crisco shortening or Crisco oil in medium skillet on medium heat.
Add green pepper, onion, garlic, cumin and thyme.
Cook and stir until browned.
Add tomato paste and chili powder.
Stir. Add a little water.
Stir.
Pour into beans.
Add rice, bacon, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Add enough water to cover by 1 1/2-inches.
Cover.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Contains 740 calories, fat 15 g (131 cal or 18% of total calories), sat fat 3 g (<5% of total calories), carb 129 g, protein 26 g, chol 5 mg and sodium 365 mg.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Press into 9x13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and put in casserole.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Combine buttermilk baking mix, milk and cheese with a wooden spoon until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously 30 seconds. Drop dough by heaping tablespoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: beef oriental
directions: Brown onions and celery in butter.
Add rice and beef and brown.
Combine next 6 ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add mixture which has been browned.
Stir in bean sprouts lightly. Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 20 minutes. Serve with noodles with soy sauce.

title: mother hershey's chocolate pudding
directions: Heat 5 cups milk to scalding.
Combine separately the cornstarch, cocoa, sugar and salt.
Stir in the 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Gradually stir the mixture into the hot milk and stir until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Serve warm or cold.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: pork chop borracho
directions: In a large frypan, fry pork chops, seasoned with salt, pepper, thyme and onion salt.
Stir in water with flour.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes.
Add beer, brown sugar and raisins.
Let simmer for half hour or until meat is tender.
Add pears on top of meat and add a bit of juice; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with small dumplings or noodles.
Yields 4 servings.

title: caramel layer chocolate bars
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine 1/3 cup evaporated milk and caramels (50) in top of double boiler. Cook over
hot
water, stirring often, until caramels melt and mixture is smooth.	Set aside.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in oil; add garlic and cook until yellow.
Add soy sauce, salt and 1/4 cup water.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook ten minutes longer.
Mix cornstarch in 1 cup cold water and add to beef mixture.
Add chopped tomatoes and cook for 5 more minutes.
Serve over hot fluffy rice.

title: christmas caramels
directions: Combine sugar, salt, corn syrup and 1/3 of the cream.
Place in saucepan and stir over moderate heat until the sugar dissolves. Reduce the heat and continue cooking, without stirring, until a candy thermometer reaches 236°.
While the syrup is cooking, heat remaining cream over hot water in a double boiler.
When the syrup reaches 236°, slowly add half of the remaining cream and let it reach 236° again.
Add remaining warm cream and cook, stirring, until the temperature reaches 242° to 244°.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well and store in jar.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Roll pastry
very
thin
to
fit
an 8-inch plate.
Set aside. Mix
apples,
apple
juice concentrate, cornstarch and spice and stir until apples are well coated.	Add lemon juice, if desired, to	keep
apples
lighter colored.	Pour into the pastry lined pie pan
and top with the second crust or pastry strips.
Seal the edges
and	cut
slits
in the top crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake
at
for
40 to 45 minutes until golden brown. Makes 8 servings.	One serving (including the crust) equals 220 calories, 1 1/2 fruit exchanges, 1 bread exchange, 2 fat exchanges.

title: perfect pot roast
directions: In 6-quart Dutch oven in hot oil, cook roast until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup of the water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender, turning occasionally.
Add vegetables.
Cover.
Cook 40 minutes or until roast and vegetables are fork-tender.
Remove roast and vegetables to platter.
Over medium heat, cook sauce until slightly thickened.
In cup, stir together flour and remaining 1/4 cup water until smooth. Gradually stir into Dutch oven.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Serve with roast.

title: stay up all night coffee cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom.
Arrange frozen rolls on top of nuts.
(Keep rolls frozen.) Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.

title: peanut butter roll candy
directions: Mix powdered sugar with just enough milk until dough consistency.
Roll out on board coated with powdered sugar. Spread with peanut butter.
Roll into a log.
Slice into 1/4-inch pieces.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugars, salt, syrup and peanuts in bowl.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir; microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and oleo; stir.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add soda; stir.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool and break into pieces.
Be sure to use glass bowl when making candy.

title: squash casserole(yellow summer squash)
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish. Top with reserved crumbs and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Mix the graham cracker crumbs, melted butter and 1/2 cup of the sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon before adding other ingredients.
Grease cookie sheet and cover with wax paper. Pour mixture in pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
While hot, roll and place in freezer for 15 minutes.
After cooling down, remove wax paper.
Spread on filling and roll again.

title: angel cherry lemon dessert(great summertime dessert.)
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with angel food slices 3/4-inch thick. Pour the 2 cans cherry or blueberry filling over the sliced angel food cake.
Mix lemon pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in sour cream; pour this over the pie filling, spreading it out so it is covered.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican goup
directions: Brown
ground beef and onion in skillet.
In large pot, add beef,
chili beans, tomato juice, rice, onion, chili mix, salt and pepper together and mix well.
If too thin, add rice (up
to 1/2 cup) to thicken.
Stir often until rice is tender and
mixture boils.
On your serving plate, place a small bed of
lettuce.
On top of that, place some Frito chips and your goup.
Sprinkle cheese on top and serve.

title: swedish almond cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening until fluffy.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar; mix well.
Combine flour and salt and stir into shortening mixture.
Add water, vanilla flavoring and nuts.
Chill dough about 1 hour, then roll into small balls and flatten.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Mix salt, vinegar and sugar.
Heat until boiling.
Pour over green tomatoes, onions, bell peppers and hot peppers.
Let set for awhile.
Put in a large pot and bring to a boil, just long enough for them to change colors.
Then seal in hot jars.

title: choc-full of chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, water and vanilla; beat well.
Add combined oats, flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and chopped milk chocolate.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes or until cookies are set.
Do not overbake.
Cool for 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack and cool completely. Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Beat together all ingredients until light and fluffy. Fill lined cupcake pans 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes. Top with about 1 teaspoon of any pie filling and return to oven for 10 minutes.
Cool and keep refrigerated.

title: tangy raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; set aside to cool.
Soften the cottage cheese with salad dressing.
Add pineapple, coconut, nuts and banana.
When gelatin begins to thicken, add the cheese mixture, then fold in the whipped cream.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: elegant dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan as crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Let cool.
Beat the cream cheese, powdered sugar and small Cool Whip and spread on crust. Prepare the pudding as directed on box. Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.
Spread the large Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle top with chopped pecans.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown hamburger lightly in skillet. Add onions, salt and pepper.
Blend soup and milk until smooth. In casserole dish, put layer of noodles and cheese.
Sprinkle parsley and meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove and top with chow mein noodles and almonds.
Brown 15 to 20 minutes.

title: magnum chili
directions: Mix together and simmer for a few hours.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain all the canned vegetables well. Add the celery, onion and green pepper. Heat the oil, sugar and vinegar to a boil. Cool it and then pour over the vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight or longer. This will keep a long time in the refrigerator.

title: frosting for banana-nut cake
directions: Cook milk and flour, stirring until thick.
Cool.
Cream Crisco, butter, powdered sugar and vanilla with mixer at high speed until light and creamy.
Add cooled flour mixture and beat fast 5 minutes longer.
This frosting is not too sweet and tastes like whipped cream.

title: pralines
directions: In a large boiler, combine sugar, milk, salt and water.
Boil to soft ball stage; add nuts and butter.
Boil to firm ball stage. Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Stir until it no longer is glossy on top.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, saute onion and celery in butter over medium heat.

Add water, potatoes, carrots and spices; cover. Reduce heat when mixture comes to boil and continue cooking over lower heat until hard vegetables become soft enough to eat with spoon, about 20 minutes.
Mash mixture with potato masher until lumpy.
Add half and half and cheese; blend in.
Continue cooking until cheese has completely melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marilyn's english pasties
directions: For dough, mix first 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add water and mix as little as necessary and use as little flour as you can when rolling out the dough.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Make a small slit in the top of each pastie.
When you remove from oven, put a little water oleo mixture into slit (1 teaspoon oleo and 1/2 teaspoon water for each pastie).
Let sit for a few minutes.

title: steak and mushroom sauce
directions: Saute onion in margarine in 8-inch skillet.
Remove from skillet with slotted spoon and set aside.
Sprinkle steaks with salt, pepper and thyme leaves and fry them in the margarine remaining from onions, add more margarine if needed.
When steaks are done as desired, remove from skillet and set aside.
Return onions to skillet and add mushrooms, saute mushrooms.
Add half and half to skillet with mushrooms and onions.
Heat sauce to boiling, stirring frequently.
Serve steaks, covered with mushroom sauce, along with Twice Baked Potatoes and Radishes and Peapods.

title: sherried chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in greased large baking dish (9 x 14-inch).
Put cheese slices over chicken.
Mix soup and sherry. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle herb seasoning over top.
Cover with melted margarine.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° or until chicken is done.

title: chicken wings with onion soup and corn syrup
directions: Wash wings very well. Put in frying pan, not fat.
Pour water over dry onion soup.
Mix well. Pour over wings.
Add corn syrup. Fry.
Use low heat and fry about 1 hour.
Add more water if necessary.
Cover at all times.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let set in fridge. over night. When ready to serve cut center out of Hawaiian Bread.
Put dip mixture in center of bread.
Slice bread from center and slice bread around dip.

title: mary's crabmeat dip
directions: Use 3/4 of crabmeat with cream cheese; blend well and make ball (with hands).
Mix 1/4 crabmeat left with sauce and pour on top.
Garnish with parsley.

title: peachy cornbread(spoon bread?)
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish. Put sour cream in a large bowl. Beat in egg and stir in butter or margarine.
Add cornbread mix and peaches.
Mix lightly just until blended.
Turn into casserole dish.
Put casserole in preheated oven at 400° and reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 65 to 70 minutes until golden brown and puffed. Serve hot from dish with large spoon. Eat with fork.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients gradually to creamed mixture, mix well.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's candies; reserve remaining candies for decorating.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Decorate tops of cookies with remaining M&M's candies.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. After baking some of the candies may be slightly cracked.
This adds texture and interest to your cookies, still the same delightful flavor.
Makes about 6 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Put all the ingredients into a large bowl and mix well.
Knead the dough until holds together in a ball.
(If the dough is too sticky, add a little more powdered milk.
Knead again.)
Make into fun thing or roll out and cut with cookie cutter, then eat it.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together, then add remaining ingredients. Mix thoroughly, using electric mixer, and pour in 2 pie shells. Bake for 50 minutes at 325°.
Keep a close watch on pies.

title: aunt sammies' pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add syrup, salt, vanilla, pecans and butter; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until filling is set.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 320°.
Put the pecan halves on top of pie.

title: corny corn bread
directions: Beat
eggs.
Add
remaining
ingredients;
mix
well. Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan (ok to use Pam).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Cut in 9 squares.
Enjoy while hot.

title: aunt zena's three "p" salad
directions: Combine at last minute before serving.

title: basic white bread
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt and butter in small saucepan.
Heat over low heat until butter melts and sugar dissolves; cool to lukewarm.

title: pina colada cream salad
directions: In a 2-quart pan, boil water; remove from heat.
Add jello's; stir until dissolved.
Add juice and rum extract.
Chill until thickened, but not set.

title: chili sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a large heavy pot.
Bring to a boil. Simmer on low heat until the liquid comes together in a smooth sauce, probably about 1 hour.
Put in jars and seal.
Try some on beans, peas, meats.
Very good!

title: cheesy broccoli tuna bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles in water for 20 minutes. Blend soup and milk into smooth sauce.
Add onions and mushrooms; drain noodles.
Layer 1 1/2 cups noodles, 1/3 cup tuna and 1 cup broccoli in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour in 1 cup sauce and repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes.
Add cheese and bake 15 more minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers. Add all ingredients except Certo. Boil 10 minutes. Remove from fire. Add Certo. Fill sterile jars and seal. Serve over block of Philadelphia cream cheese. Dip with crackers.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into 4 portions.
Mix flour and salt.
Pound into meat.
Set aside remaining flour.
Brown meat in small amount hot shortening.
Place meat in shallow baking dish.
Blend remaining flour with drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Pour over meat.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours or until tender.
Top with cheese.
Return to oven for a few minutes. Serves 4.

title: reese's peanut butter candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine in microwave. Spread on top of mixture; refrigerate or place in freezer for 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: orange chocolate chip cookies
directions: Grate 1 1/2 teaspoons of the colored zest from the orange and squeeze 2 tablespoons juice.
Combine the flour, soda and salt. Beat butter, sugars and orange zest until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk, vanilla and orange juice.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips with a spoon.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, about 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake until edges start to brown.
Let stand on baking sheets for 1 minute and remove to wire racks.

title: snowballs
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Shape into walnut size balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: diet cheesecake
directions: Make jello as directed.
Blend with cottage cheese until smooth in blender.
Mix altogether and let set like regular jello.

title: luscious flan
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar into heavy saucepan.
Place over medium heat, cooking, stirring constantly until sugar melts and syrup is light golden brown.
Pour syrup into 6-oz. custard cups.
Let cool. Combine milks in medium saucepan and heat until bubble from around edges of pan.
Combine egg substitute, 1/4 cup sugar and almond extract.
Beat well.
Gradually stir about 1 cup hot milk into egg mixture.
Add remaining milk, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture evenly into custard cups.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Place custard cups in shallow pan and pour hot water to depth of 1 inch into pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Remove cups from water, and chill at least 4 hours.
To serve, loosen edges of custard with spatula, invert onto plates.
Arrange assorted fresh fruits around the sides.
Yield:
6 servings (154 calories per serving with 1/3 cup fruit).

title: pecan bits
directions: Blend altogether at low speed.
Press into small muffin tins.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil whole chicken until the meat falls off the bones.
Remove skin and bones.
Keep meat in broth over medium heat.
Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and green onions in butter.
Add this to the chicken.
Cut up the smoked sausage into bite-size pieces and add to the pot.
Add the eggs (whole).
Add desired spices. Allow pot to simmer.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Combine flour, milk and 1 cup sugar. Pour over butter.
(Cook or let come to a boil the peaches and sugar.)
Pour over batter.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Do not stir as you pour in pan.
(If peaches are not juicy enough, add some water.
Don't have cobbler too dry.)

title: double butterscotch drop cookies
directions: Cream together butter or lard and dry pudding until fluffy. Beat in brown sugar, eggs and vinegar.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Fold in pecans and butterscotch morsels.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about walnut size and flatten out a little with wet fork on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° about 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Add broth and heat to boiling.
Add noodles, salt and pepper.
Heat for 3 minutes.
Add frozen broccoli and cook for about 5 minutes.
Add cubed cheese and cook until melted.
Add milk after pan has been removed from heat.

title: four cheese macaroni
directions: In a large pot of boiling water, cook pasta for 8 to 10 minutes, until tender.
Drain and return to pot.
Add milk, cheeses and white pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until the cheeses are melted.

title: tomato soup for company
directions: Add together, simmer.
Serve with plain croutons.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well. Chill thoroughly.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on a pizza pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Mix milk and lemon juice until thickened.
Mix in cream cheese until well blended.
Spread on cooled cookie dough.
Place fruit on as desired:
strawberries, kiwi fruit, bananas, grapes, peaches, etc.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Arrange apple slices in dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over apples.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cook at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mushroom meat balls
directions: Mix soup with water.
Add 1/4 cup soup/water to ground beef. Add egg, bread crumbs, onion, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Shape into small balls.
Brown in 1 tablespoon canola oil then pour remaining soup/water over meat balls and simmer 25 minutes.

title: strawberry salad deluxe
directions: To gelatin, add 2 cups boiling water, then all the remaining ingredients, except for sour cream.
Place half the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill for 1 hour.
Spread sour cream over mixture; add remaining gelatin, fruit and nut mixture.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onions and chops.
Brown lightly on both sides.
Put sliced potatoes in buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange chops over potatoes.
Add soup and milk to onions in skillet.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over chops.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for 30 to 40 minutes until potatoes are done.

title: almond slices
directions: Mix to a froth, eggs, oil, vanilla and sugar.
Add to the mixture of flour, baking powder and salt.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Shape into 2 long narrow rolls and bake at 350° for 30 minutes on a greased cookie sheet.
Let cool slightly, then cut into 3/4-inch slices and put under broiler to brown on each side.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas. Mix thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients, mixing well. Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stoney's pound cake
directions: Mix all together until smooth and creamy.
Grease and flour large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Test with broomstraw until broomstraw comes out clean.

title: fran's ham loaf
directions: Dissolve over heat; pour over loaf.
Baste twice during last hour of cooking.
Serves 10.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook chicken in seasoned water in a large pot.
Remove chicken.
Boil noodles 8 to 10 minutes.
Cube meat.
Mix chicken, noodles and peas.
Make smooth mixture of mayo and dressing.
Mix in.
Stir all of Parmesan cheese and add olives.
(You need large mixing bowl.
Keeps ten days in refrigerator.)

title: fireside coffee mix
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
In a cup of boiling water, measure out the amount of mixture to suit your taste.

title: tea muffins (low calorie)
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon together.
Add flakes.
Beat egg and add water and Sweet & Low and salad oil. Stir in dry ingredients, mix well as possible.
Add raisins.
Line muffin pans with paper liners.
Divide batter evenly in muffin pans for 12.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Slice carrots, potatoes and onions.
Put in dish.
Salt and pepper.
Place pork chops on top. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour soup over mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tindall goulash
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cook macaroni.
Grease casserole with butter. Layer 1/2 macaroni, Velveeta, hamburger, corn, tomatoes, other 1/2 of macaroni and top with Velveeta.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salmon loaf(with egg and english pea sauce)
directions: Drain salmon and reserve liquid, then break fish into small pieces.
Mix with all other ingredients until well blended.
Shape into a loaf and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Slice and serve hot with egg and pea sauce.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Mix all of this together in a bowl.

title: hurry up biscuits
directions: Mix together well.
Put on floured board.
Knead a little and make small balls.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes.
A good morning biscuit!

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: In 10 or 12-inch skillet, cook beef until browned.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, water, vegetables and Worcestershire.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° until hot and bubbling (10 to 15 minutes).
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Remove dish from oven.
Stir; arrange biscuits on top of hot mixture and top with cheese.
Bake until biscuits are golden brown.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar and sugar.
Shake well.
Slice cucumbers and onion.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and dill weed.
Let stand for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 10 x 5-inch cookie sheet and line with wax paper.
Mix ingredients and pour on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto towel sprinkled with 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Pull off wax paper.
Roll like a cinnamon roll in towel. Cool in fridge.
Unroll, fill with filling and reroll.

title: clam cakes
directions: Sift flour in big bowl.
Beat egg and add to flour.
Add salt and baking powder.
Add strained clams (save clam juice).
Add milk to clam juice to equal 1 cup of liquid.
Mix liquid in with dry ingredients.
Add milk as needed until it's a little thicker than pancake batter.
Shape into small cakes.
Fry in vegetable oil until golden brown.

title: easy and delicious sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken
in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer jam or preserves, onion soup mix and pineapple slices.
Pour salad dressing over top.
Let set for several hours.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: david's taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except relish and salad dressing.
Mix jalapeno relish and salad dressing until pinkish in color.
Pour over salad and toss.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion and drain well.
Mix in soups and seasonings.
Simmer for about 30 minutes, covered.
(I use electric skillet.)
Cook enough spaghetti or noodles to feed your family.
A few minutes before serving, stir sour cream into meat sauce and heat through; do not boil.
Serve sauce over pasta.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix eagle brand milk and kool-aid together, then add cool whip and mix together until blended.
Pour over into crust. Refrigerate.

title: family reunion baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in twice their volume of water.
