Rinse beans and cook in Dutch oven until just soft (about 30 minutes). If your water is hard, add 2 Tbsp. soda during cooking.
Put all other ingredients in crockpot, stir and cook on low setting for 30 minutes.
Add cooked beans and cook at low temperature until beans are dark brown, 6 to 8 hours.

title: orange-coconut apple crisp(microwave)
directions: Arrange apples in an 8-inch square glass baking dish. Sprinkle with orange juice.
Combine brown sugar, flour and orange rind in bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly, using pastry blender.
Add coconut and toss to mix. Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over apples.

title: chicken and cheese enchilada
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In center of each tortilla, place 1/4 cup chicken, 2 tablespoons cheese and 1 tablespoon salsa; roll up. Arrange seam side down in 8-inch square baking dish.
Top with remaining salsa and cheese.
Bake 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together the shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients and add nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoons 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Yields 3 dozen.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
In large saucepan, boil water; add cabbage.
Cook until half done.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.
Add more water if needed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hawaiian haystack
directions: Melt butter in microwave.
Add flour, stir in milk.
Cook on High for about 8 minutes or until thick and glossy, stirring every 3 minutes.

title: tuna pot pie
directions: In skillet, melt margarine.
Add chopped onion.
Stir occasionally for 3 minutes.
Add thawed peas and carrots, tuna and beans.
Cook for 1 minute.
Stir in soup mix blended with milk. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce to low and simmer, uncovered, 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted.
Pour into 2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Twist corn twists to form lattice design over top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until corn twists are done.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: First, cream the butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and salt and mix well. Stir in potato chips and pecans. Drop from spoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
With spoon dipped in water, flatten each cookie. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix flour, butter, 1/3 cup corn syrup, the granulated sugar and salt in large bowl.
Spread evenly in pan.
Blend cream cheese until smooth. Beat in eggs until well blended.
Beat in 1 cup corn syrup and the vanilla until smooth.
Pour over dough.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until edges are light brown and filling is set.
Spread with jam. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Cut into 2-inch bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage, chop onions and set aside.
Remove seasoning package and save.
Saute noodles in small amount of butter.
Toast sunflower seeds and almonds until lightly browned.
Add cooled noodles, sunflower seeds and almonds to cabbage, toss to mix. Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and seasoning in small bowl.
Mix well with whisk.
Pour over cabbage.
Chill.

title: beef with sour cream
directions: Remove bone and fat from steak.
Cut meat into thin, narrow strips.
Dredge in flour; using large skillet, quickly brown meat on all sides in hot oil.
Add onions, broth, thyme, mushrooms, liquid from mushrooms and peas.
Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes. Stir in sour cream.
Heat through; do not boil.
Serve over hot rice.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir all the ingredients together.
Let set in fridge for 24 hours.
Cook at 350° to 400° for 20 minutes.
Will keep in fridge for 5 to 6 weeks.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare your favorite pastry.
Stir together sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix with apples.
Turn into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Dot with butter.
Unfold pie crust over fruit; fold edges under just inside edge of pan.
Bake 1 hour or until juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.

title: icebox cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Combine dessert topping mix with milk and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Add cream cheese and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Add pineapple.
Frost cake with this mixture.
Refrigerate until served.

title: chocolate cashew butter
directions: Blend or grind nuts until fine in blender or food processor. Add half of the butter.
Cover and blend about 3 minutes more or until mixture is spreadable.
Scrape down sides as necessary. Transfer mixture to a small mixing bowl.
In small saucepan, melt remaining butter and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Dissolve coffee in the water.
Stir chocolate and coffee into nut mixture.
Makes 1 cup.

title: hungarian coffee cake pull apart rolls
directions: Heat 1/2 cup brown sugar, 3 tablespoons cream and 3/4 stick margarine.
Bring to boil and pour in ungreased Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Sprinkle in it 1 cup pecans or less.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and with
tongs or fingers, dip frozen balls in margarine.
Then roll in mixture of 1/2 cup white sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Place in pan, stacking haphazardly.
Cover with cloth.
Set in cold oven and by morning, they should be ready to bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: snowball treats
directions: Thoroughly mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Add corn flakes.
Shape into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar and coconut.
Chill or serve immediately.

title: cream curry vegetable crisp
directions: One and one-half cups, or one can of corn, one cup cracker crumbs, salt and pepper to taste, three eggs beaten separately and cream to make soft.
Bake in buttered pan.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish combine ingredients.
Brush chicken with bitter and salt & pepper. Place chicken on top of rice. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until chicken is tender.

title: rich and meaty chili
directions: In frying pan, brown ground beef; drain.
Put drained beef and remaining ingredients into a 6-quart pot.
Cover the pot.
Let simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: no bake pumpkin cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, sugar, spice, milk, egg and pumpkin in a saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil. Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes. Stir twice.
Pour into pie shell and chill 4
hours in refrigerator.
Garnish with whipped cream and nuts.

title: mushroom baked chicken
directions: Shake pieces of chicken in flour mixture until coated.
Brown in frying pan with shortening or oil so it doesn't burn.
Place pieces, when browned, in a roaster.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cut up cranberry sauce; fold in whipped cream, mayonnaise and other ingredients.
Freeze.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: settlers beans
directions: Brown bacon, beef and onion; drain. Drain beans and add to meat mixture. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy beef burgundy
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Use heavy casserole or Dutch oven.
Add all ingredients except mushrooms.
Stir slightly to mix.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Add mushrooms about an hour before serving.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: garlic lovers pasta and chickpeas
directions: Drain and rinse chickpeas.
Set aside.
Cook macaroni according to directions.
While macaroni is cooking, heat the olive oil and margarine in a small saucepan.
Add cayenne pepper and stir until blended.
Add minced garlic and saute on low heat until garlic is soft.
Then add chickpeas and coat well.
Keep warm.

title: hill of beans salad
directions: Put bacon in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove bacon and place on towels to drain.
Blend sugar and cornstarch with bacon drippings.
Stir in salt, pepper and vinegar. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, until thick.
Add drained beans, onion and celery slices to sauce in casserole, stirring well.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Preheat before serving.
Even better the next day.
Makes 4 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove bones and skin from salmon; drain and flake (reserve liquid.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a well-greased baking dish or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until center is solid.
Serve hot with Egg Sauce.

title: key lime macadamia dream pie
directions: To make crust, combine cookie crumbs, finely chopped nuts, sugar and melted butter.
Press into a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate using the back of a spoon.
Chill.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Crush wafers and add all ingredients.
Stir until moist.
Form in 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail
directions: Cut enough fruit to fill large Tupperware cake taker, 8 to 10 quarts.
Use medium or heavy syrup.
This will make about 18 pints. Add 1 maraschino cherry, cut in half, to each pint.
Process 15 minutes in pressure cooker at 5 pounds or for the fruit that takes the longest in your fruit cocktail.
Use sterilized jars and raw pack.

title: cowboy burger
directions: Butter insides of split buns; place butter side down in hot frying pan to brown.
Heat chili in small saucepan.
Shape meat into round patty 1/2 inch thick and place next to bun in middle of hot pan, turning only once when the red juices seep to the top. Place bun halves on a warm platter, browned sides up.
When other side of patty has been seared, slip meat onto the bun and cover with the hot chili beans.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and top off with raw onions.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in kettle, drain. Add remaining
ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: clam chowder
directions: Melt the margarine in a deep saucepan.
Add onion; cook slowly until golden brown.
Add clams in liquid.
Skim if necessary.
Add potatoes, salt and black pepper to taste.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Remove the mixture from heat and slowly add milk and cream which have been heated.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: toasted coconut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add wet ingredients all at once. Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch greased loaf tin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.
As an alternative, pour into muffin tins and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf or 12 muffins.

title: chocolate easter eggs
directions: Boil potato until tender. Remove from water. Let stand to cool. Mash and add sugar until firm. May add nuts, cherries or dried fruits. Roll into shape.
Cover with melted chocolate. Makes 6 servings.

title: percolator punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, cranberry juice, water and brown sugar in a large 30 cup coffee pot.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Place all in a zip lock bag and marinate for 24 hours chilled. Enjoy.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and melt again.
Add cream and allow to boil one minute.
Remove from heat, beat in powdered sugar and add vanilla.

title: red crab soup
directions: Place water in large stockpot.
Bring to a boil.
Add first 5 ingredients.
Return to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add potatoes.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes more.
Add tomatoes, paste and water (2 cups).
Simmer 10 minutes.
Drain peas and add with crab meat.
Simmer 10 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 10 more minutes.
Serve hot.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water.
Drain and mash the potatoes. Add the butter or oleo and the milk (like you make mashed potatoes, or use leftovers).
Add all other ingredients.
Mix in enough salad dressing or mayonnaise to make it moist.
Add more salt, if needed.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix beef, onion, 1 cup water and garlic.
Cook on 100% power in a 3-quart microwave dish for 5 minutes.
Stir once.
Cook, covered, on 50% power (Medium) for 20 to 24 minutes, or until beef is tender; stir once.
Skim off the fat grease.
Stir in rest of water, tomatoes, paprika, chili powder, seasoned salt and soy sauce.
Cook, covered, on High for about 4 minutes, or until heated through.
Mix sour cream and flour; slowly stir in 1 cup of the hot mixture.
Mix all.
Put in casserole.
Cook, uncovered, on High for about 6 minutes.

title: oven meatball stew
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients; shape into meatballs.
Brown in hot oil.
Place in casserole dish.
Add 1 tablespoon flour to oil and add tomato juice.
Pour over meatballs; place diced vegetables on top.
Salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Then add water.
Cook until all thickens.
Serve on bread or biscuits.

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Saute onion and garlic in vegetable oil; cut steak in cubes and flour with dry seasonings.
Brown meat in oil with onion and garlic until all sides of meat brown and flour is saturated.
Add can of consomme and Worcestershire sauce; stir as it thickens. Add 1 more can of any liquid.
Gravy and meat should simmer at least 1 hour.
Add peeled, pared and sliced vegetables.
Cook 1 to 2 more hours.
Add water if too thick.
Should be beefy and thick.

title: chicken rosemary
directions: Dip each piece of meat into margarine.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper.
Place in shallow pan that has been greased.
Sprinkle lightly with rosemary.
Add a small amount of water to cover bottom of the pan; cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: italian dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shake in a covered container and chill.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Place chopped rhubarb in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Mix jello and sugar; sprinkle over rhubarb.
Now, put a layer of marshmallows over this.
Mix yellow cake by the directions on box.
Pour this over all ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This is very easy and very, very good!

title: real good white fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved and reaches a boil. Boil for 10 to 15 minutes to softball stage (238° candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm about 45 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat until begins to lose its gloss and holds its shape.
Stir in nuts and cherries.
Turn into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: caramel coconut pie
directions: Melt butter; add coconut and pecans. Cook until golden; set aside and cool. Combine cream cheese and milk; beat well until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip. Layer 1/4 mixture in pie crust, then 1/4 caramel topping, then layer 1/4 coconut, pecan and butter mixture. Then repeat. (Makes 2 pies.)

title: string bean casserole
directions: Combine drained beans and cream of mushroom soup; pour into a baking dish.
Sprinkle and cover onion rings over bean mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly hot.
Serve hot.

title: magic marshmallow crescent puffs
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Separate rolls into 16 triangles. Dip marshmallow in melted margarine, then roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Wrap a triangle around each marshmallow, squeezing edges of dough tightly to seal.
Dip in margarine and place margarine side down in deep muffin cups.
Place on foil or cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately. Top with glaze.

title: baked yam and cranberry casserole
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar, orange slices, orange juice and pecans in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 375°.
Place yams on top and bake another 20 minutes.
Try using freshly peeled yams.
Place chunk yams in casserole and add in this order:
cranberries, orange juice and slices, sugar and salt and bake until done (about 45 minutes to 1 hour) at 375°.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Remove bone from leg of lamb;
mix Sauce.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine celery and onion with beer.
Cook until tender.
Add ketchup, mustard, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Great Sloppy Joes!

title: apple pudding
directions: Fill buttered baking dish with sliced apples.
Pour over top the batter made with remaining ingredients.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven until brown.
Some like to eat this with cinnamon and milk over it.

title: chocolate covered rice krispies treats
directions: In a large pot, over medium heat, mix the sugar and Karo syrup together.
Heat until sugar is liquified.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Mix together.
Fold in the Rice Krispies, mixing until they are all covered.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Flatten evenly into pan, using wax paper.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: In a warm bowl, add yeast, water, sugar, salt and Crisco. With your hand, mix a small amount of flour to yeast mixture.
Add flour until you have a soft dough.
Knead in bowl 50 times.
Let rise double.
Punch down.
Put on dough board.
Pat out with your hand or roll out and cut.
Put melted butter on each biscuit and fold over.
Place on a greased pan and bake at 400° until done.

title: chex mix snack
directions: Melt oleo in pan (use oblong roasting pan).
Mix all ingredients well; put in oven.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Good holiday snack.

title: custard pie
directions: Thoroughly mix eggs, salt, nutmeg, sugar and vanilla.
Slowly stir in hot milk.
Pour at once into pie shell. Add dash of nutmeg on top of custard before baking.
Bake in hot oven at 475° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425° and bake 10 minutes longer or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and serve in a round of bread or a purple cabbage that is cut out for a bowl.

title: shrimp and tortellini
directions: Boil shrimp in Old Bay seasoning until cooked.
Peel shrimp. Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and set aside. Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat; add minced shallot and basil.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add shrimp, pasta and cheese.
Toss gently.
Yields 4 servings.

title: emma doherty's sugar cookies
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs and half and half or milk if dough is too dry.
Add vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients, eggs and vanilla together.

title: heavenly pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs until slightly frothy; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked cream cheese pie shell.
Should make 2 pies.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip after it has cooled.

title: stay a bed stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a casserole.
Cover tight with foil or a lid.
Bake in a 275° oven for 5 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fire house round steak and coca-cola gravy
directions: Dice onion and cook in skillet with corn oil until soft. Remove from skillet, cut round steak into 1 x 2-inch cubes and brown in skillet.
Add onion, tomato sauce and Coca-Cola, stir. Drop steak in and bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cover.
Cook about 2 hours, or until steak is tender enough to cut with a fork.
Remove lid and thicken gravy as desired by cooking openly.
This may be served as steak, gravy with rice or creamed potatoes.

title: booger hollow biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together until nice and smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen biscuits.

title: chicken and mushroom quesadillas
directions: Cook mushrooms in 1 tablespoon butter until tender. Add green onions and chicken and mix well. Butter one side of a tortilla. I place mine butter side down on my George Foreman grill, but you can also place the tortilla in a large frying pan. Place half of chicken mixture on tortilla. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cheese and Season-All. Place another buttered tortilla on top (butter side up). Close grill and cook for 2 to 3 minutes or if pan-frying, brown on one side, flip (good luck!) and brown the other side. Use remaining tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese to cook another quesadilla. Cut quesadillas into wedges with a pizza cutter and serve with sour cream.

title: cheese mix
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Serve with crackers or Triscuits.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix and pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift and add flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add oatmeal, chopped nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's bread pudding
directions: Soak cubed dry bread in scalded milk, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add sugar, butter, salt, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Mix very well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking pan or glass baking dish.
Bake at 325° in pan for 1 hour or at 300° in baking dish for 1 hour until firm.
Cool and eat warm, add added touch if wanted, 1/2 cup chopped apples.
This is an excellent pudding from generations.

title: fantastic fondue
directions: Mix milk and cream cheese in electric mixer.
Heat in saucepan and add garlic salt.
Slowly add Parmesan cheese and stir until smooth.
Transfer to fondue pot and keep heat on low.
Serve with cubed French bread and veggies.

title: citrus fruit salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until well blended.
Pour mixture into a bottle; refrigerate up to 1 month.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add tomato sauce and seasoning.
Add 2 cups of water.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put small amount of sauce on bottom.
Layer sauce, uncooked noodles, cottage cheese and grated cheeses until full (usually 3 full layers).
Top with extra sauce and cheese.
Bake, covered, at 325° until cheese bubbles.
Serves 10.

title: pumpkin chiffon dessert
directions: Cut soft butter into the flour. Add chopped pecans. Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: golden lamb celery seed dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add onion. Add small amount of oil. Mix well. Gradually add small amount of vinegar and oil, alternating, ending with oil, beating well. Use mixer or blender.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in one 9-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar over butter and arrange pineapple in pan. Sift into one bowl flour, sugar and shortening.
Use slightly over 1/2 of the milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining milk, egg and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili chicken
directions: Boil chicken and save broth water. After chicken is done; debone and boil spaghetti noodles in broth water. When spaghetti is done, drain, and add the remaining ingredients.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well and bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Cream the butter with brown sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add melted chocolate chips, coffee powder and rum.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Top with a few walnuts after baking.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix ingredients well in a pint jar or container.
Refrigerate for a few days before using. The longer kept, the thicker and better. May be served on lettuce, Waldorf or fruit salad, cabbage slaw or shredded carrots and raisins.

title: company potatoes
directions: Melt margarine, soup and cream cheese.
Layer 1/2 potatoes into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 can of mushrooms, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese.
Layer rest of the potatoes, mushrooms and sauce. Place the rest of the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wyoming salad
directions: Make slaw from grated cabbage, carrot and onion.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg. Add melted butter, then cream; mix well. Stir in cubed bread and raisins. Let stand 10 to 15 minutes. Pour into well-greased deep pan, 9 x 13. Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown. Pour Butter Vanilla Sauce over pudding.

title: easy pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together well. There are 2 ways to use mixture.
Bake this way; use 2 loaf pans (9 x 5-inch), greased and floured and bake for 1 1/4 hours.
Or, use three 1-pound coffee cans, greased and floured, and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
If using coffee cans, omit water in your mixture.
Also, when using coffee cans, after cooling, use knife around tins to loosen bread.
They may be hot when coming out of cans so be careful.

title: mickie's waffles
directions: Sift cake flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together.
Add milk, eggs and butter.
Mix well with wire whisk or spoon.

title: "mock" kentucky fried chicken
directions: Wipe chicken dry. Combine dressing, flour, lemon juice, salt and butter into paste and coat chicken evenly. Stack pieces in bowl and cover to marinate.
Combine pancake mix with spices. Dip chicken pieces into milk, then into pancake mix. Dust off excess. Heat oil and fry until brown.
Place in shallow pan and put remaining milk over.
Seal with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 10 minutes at 400°. Baste again with milk during the last 10 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail dream cake
directions: In large bowl, mix together cake mix, fruit cocktail and eggs; beat well.
Bake in greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack or serving plate to complete cooling.
Top with lemon glaze.

title: yiayia's spanakopita(spinach pie)
directions: Brown onion in olive oil.
Beat eggs and add to spinach. Break up Feta cheese in crumbled pieces and mix with cottage cheese.
Add to spinach.
Add browned onions; season with pepper. Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and place 10 sheets phyllo into pan, brushing each with melted butter.
Spread spinach mixture on top. Cover with 10 sheets of phyllo, buttering each phyllo as you add it.
Butter top well and cut into squares about 2 x 3-inches.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: large spiced pound cake
directions: Mix butter and shortening until soft. Blend in nutmeg and vanilla. Stir in sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in flour. Grease and flour the bottom of a tube pan. Only use a 10-inch tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or less at 325 degrees.

title: nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread on platter.
Layer remaining ingredients in order.
Serve with corn/Tostitos chips.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight.

title: green slime(a fast one dish salad)
directions: Mix together in square 9-inch dish.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Could be made the night before.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Chop pepper, onion and eggplant into small pieces and brown in 3 tablespoons butter or olive oil.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, brown sugar, Cheddar cheese and bread crumbs.
Simmer all of the ingredients until thickened.
Pour into greased casserole dish and cover with grated Cheddar cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a heavy saucepan, combine peanut butter and butter and warm over low heat, stirring until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and eggs, beating by hand until mixed.
Mix baking powder, salt and flour and add to the dough.
Stir in vanilla.
Pat dough onto a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Place Hershey bars over the hot, baked pastry.
Let melt and spread evenly.
Cool before cutting into squares.
Store airtight.
Makes 36.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Cover pie shell with sliced bananas. Pour in chocolate pudding mix. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate for at least an hour and serve. Great for diabetics.

title: coconut chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Combine eggs, coconut, flour and milk to make batter.
Dredge chicken in batter to coat. Fry chicken pieces in oil until golden brown, turning often. Drain on paper towel or brown paper bag.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Reheat at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: puffy omelet(makes about 4 servings)
directions: Separate
yolks
from
whites and beat yolks with milk, salt and pepper until foamy.
Fold in stiffly beaten whites.

title: nanny's dumplings
directions: Boil hen to make good rich broth.
Mix ingredients together and work it together until it can be rolled out thin.
Cut dough into small pieces (approximately 1 1/2 x 2-inches).
Have broth in a rolling boil and drop dumplings in broth, one at a time, shaking boiler frequently; do not stir.
If broth is hot enough dumplings should be done in 4 or 5 minutes.
Put deboned chicken pieces in broth before adding dumplings to broth.
This will feed family of 6 to 8.
Good luck!

title: peach topped coffee cake
directions: Cream together 1/4 cup Crisco and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine the 1 cup flour, brown sugar, salt and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Stir in the creamed mixture alternating with the milk.
Spread the batter evenly in a greased and floured pan. Arrange peaches on top of batter.
Combine the 1/3 cup flour, brown sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cut in Crisco and nuts. Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Store in tight container.
Use 2 to 3 tablespoons per cup of water.
Heat water first if using microwave, then add mix.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Hollow
out centers of squash and place in baking dish. Combine
meat,
bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper in a mixing bowl.
Stuff into squash.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over
stuffed squash.
Bake in 375° oven until tender (usually 45 minutes).

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Mix
together
brown
sugar,
flour
and
salt	for the coating on pork chops.
After you have put this dry mixture on pork
chops, mix the soy sauce, vinegar and water together and pour
over	pork
chops that you have placed in a baking dish. Chop
bell	pepper	and
onions;
sprinkle	evenly	over meat. Cover with foil.
Cook for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: halibut steaks
directions: Stir together dressing and mustard.
Brush 1/4 cup sauce on both sides of fish; reserve remaining sauce.
Arrange fish in an 8-inch square baking dish with thickest portions toward outside of dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and vent.
Microwave on High 4 to 7 minutes, turning dish after 3 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 2 to 3 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serve with remaining sauce.
Serves 4.

title: eggplant-grilled with fresh herbs
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and let stand for 1/2 hour to season oil.
Wash eggplant and trim top and bottom.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices; do not peel.
Arrange on a platter in single layer.
Sprinkle both sides with salt and let sit about 30 minutes to remove bitterness.
Light the grill.
With a cloth or paper towel, wipe the grate with oil (corn oil is preferable to olive oil which burns easily).
Place eggplant directly on the grate.
As the eggplant starts to score, (pick up the lines of the grate) brush lightly with the prepared marinade.
Flip and brush again.
Just before removing from grill, top each slice with tomato and cheese. Serve hot as side dish or entree with bread and salad.

title: baked pork chops in vermouth
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pork chops in 9 x 11-inch pan. Arrange mushrooms and onion around the chops.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and coffee evenly on the pork chops.
Add vermouth until it comes up to the edge of the chops but does not cover.
Place in oven and bake for 45 minutes.
When chops are done, remove from pan and place mushrooms, onions and remaining liquid in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and add cornstarch solution.
Cook until thickened.
Place some of the sauce on a plate with a pork chop on top.
Garnish with chopped parsley and serve with a Rice Pilaf.
Sauteed cinnamon apples also goes great.

title: garlic pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers, onions and salt with ice; let soak 3 hours. Pour off water. Mix remaining ingredients. Add cucumbers and onions to vinegar mixture. Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 or 10 minutes. Fill hot jars and add 1 clove garlic, 1 sprig dill or 1 teaspoon dill seed. Seal jars and let stand for a few days.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, mix well.
Fold in flour and milk.
Add extract.
Place batter in a well greased bundt pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: grilled catfish
directions: Mix olive oil and sesame seed.
Brush fillets with mixture. Place on hot grill.
Cook 5 or 6 minutes on each side.
Add salt, pepper and lemon juice to fish before removing from grill.

title: company salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ice water, drained pineapple (reserve juice), bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into a large, flat dish.
Chill until firm.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Combine water and spaghetti sauce in bowl.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Arrange layer of uncooked noodles, slightly overlapping, on top of sauce.
Spread 1/2 the Ricotta and 1/2 the Mozzarella over noodles.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Add another layer of sauce.
Repeat with another layer of noodles, the remaining Ricotta and Mozzarella and 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Top with layer of noodles. Pour remaining sauce over, spreading evenly to cover edges of noodles.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup
Parmesan.
Cover tightly with foil.
Set on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until knifes goes easily through pasta.
Let stand, covered, on rack for 10 minutes.

title: potato and mozzarella pie
directions: Peel, cook and mash the potatoes.
Season with butter, salt and pepper.
Butter a deep pie plate. Sprinkle lightly with flour and spread the mashed potatoes on the bottom.
Cut cheese into 1/2-inch slices and arrange half the slices on the potatoes.

Cut the tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices and arrange all of them on the cheese. Sprinkle with oregano, basil, salt and pepper. On top, arrange rest of Mozzarella and Parmesan and pour over all the melted butter.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: minnesota loganberries(better known as baked beans)
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Then add soda.
Boil for 10 minutes. Drain and add rest of ingredients and enough water to cover. Pressure cook 15 pounds for 30 minutes or bake 6 to 8 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, vanilla, eggs, sugar and vegetable oil.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and cream of tartar.

title: cream cheese & chicken
directions: Mix cream cheese and soups, then add chicken. Put in a 8 x 8 dish and cover with crumbled Ritz crackers and butter mixture. Bake at 350 for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, then drain.
Combine eggs, milk, soup, mayonnaise and cheese, saving some cheese to mix with cracker crumbs.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Crumble Ritz or Town House crackers and add the remaining cheese.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook until soft ball in water.
Beat until it begins to set and add parched peanuts.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Split and rinse chicken breasts and remove any skin.
Dry chicken on paper towels.
Slice mushrooms and mince 1 garlic clove.
Begin cooking linguine according to directions on box.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, cornmeal, vanilla, butter and vinegar. Mix well.
Let sit for 10 minutes, then stir gently.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put potatoes in 1 1/2-quart ovenproof casserole with 1 tablespoon oil.
Mix other ingredients and pour over potatoes. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle top with corn flakes or potato chips.
Dot with butter.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save juice and add to Jell-O, orange juice, hot water and cranberry sauce.
Chill until Jell-O is slightly thick.
Add then pineapple, celery and pecans.
Refrigerate for several more hours.

title: cherry kucha
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in margarine with blender.
Set aside 1 cup of the crumb mixture.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add this mixture to larger crumb mixture and mix. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon pie filling on top.
Sprinkle with cup of reserved crumbs. Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: tuna eggs
directions: Boil eggs until done.
Separate egg yolk from egg white.
Mix mayo, salt, pepper, sweet pickles, sugar and tuna together with egg yolk, then place ball of mixture into egg whites.

title: party mix
directions: Toss all ingredients and bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir mix every 15 minutes.

title: kumquat pie
directions: Beat Cool Whip and condensed milk, add lemon juice, beat until thick. Add kumquats. Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.

title: overnight egg casserole
directions: Place bread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese; set aside.
Brown sausage and drain.
Sprinkle over cheese and bread.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard and soup; pour over mixture. Cover and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: incredible "hulk" punch
directions: Cut sherbet in several pieces.
Put in punch bowl; add juice and ale.
Stir often.
(Yes, it's green.)

title: peppy potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1-inch wedges.
Pour coating mix into a plastic bag; add salt.
Dip potatoes in melted butter and place in bag and shake.
Place potatoes on a well-greased baking sheet and bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: hershey chocolate bar pie
directions: Break up candy bars in a bowl.
Microwave until melted.
Add 1/2 of the Cool Whip and stir.
Spread into cookie crust.
Cover the pie with the rest of the Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: cabbage
directions: Cook the cabbage for 5 minutes. Add the sour cream and the dry mustard.
Mix and let set for awhile before serving.

title: chili sauce meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, salt, pepper, paprika, Worcestershire sauce, corn flakes and eggs.
Roll into balls.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Mix chili sauce, grape jelly and lemon juice.
Add meatballs and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: fresh sauteed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and wash mushrooms thoroughly.
Melt margarine in heavy skillet with lid.
Place mushrooms in skillet, then add all ingredients.
Stir and cook on low with lid for approximately 30 minutes. Serve with grilled steaks.
Ingredients should be adjusted to satisfy individual taste.

title: connie's cornflake cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add rind and eggs, then milk and flour alternately.
Then add cornflakes, raisins and nuts (grated coconut, optional).
Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Make pie shell.
Heat chocolate pieces, milk and butter in 1-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Set aside.

title: broccoli, cauliflower, tomato casserole
directions: Steam broccoli and cauliflower 3 or 4 minutes.
Break into bite-size pieces.
Drain well.
Add cherry tomatoes, soup and cubed cheese.
Mix gently.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart round casserole dish.
Top with stuffing mix and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Stir baking mix, milk and cheese until mixture forms soft balls.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Combine butter and garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits.

title: cheesy ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix ham, cheese, broccoli and soup in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir remaining ingredients until dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls over broccoli mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Makes 4 large servings.

title: corn bread - fluffy
directions: Mix well and bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and chocolate.
Stir in milk, butter and egg yolks.
Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Make meringue of 4 egg whites and sugar.
Brown in oven.

title: dilled cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumbers and onion in a shallow serving dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: potato and onion bake
directions: Wash white baking potatoes (about 4); slice thin and put in glass baking dish.
Slice onion thin and put on top of potatoes. Sprinkle with garlic powder, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Dot with 1/2 stick of margarine.
Cook in microwave (covered with Saran Wrap) for about 7 minutes.
Take out.
Uncover carefully and stir. Re-cover and cook about 7 to 8 minutes more.
Let sit covered for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: apricot carrot bread *
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with cooking spray.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In medium size bowl, combine beaten egg, sugar, applesauce, carrots and vegetable oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened (batter will be thick).
Fold in apricots.
Pour batter into pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Wrap loaf and store overnight before slicing.

title: turkey sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground turkey, onion and pepper in a frying pan sprayed with nonfat
cooking spray.
When brown, drain meat and rinse with hot water.
Also rinse the pan with hot water.
Return meat to pan.
Pour on the Manwich sauce.
Warm until ready to serve.

title: microwave lo-cal chicken cacciatore
directions: Place chicken breasts in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Combine mushrooms, tomatoes, green peppers, onion, wine, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Cook covered at Medium-high for 20 minutes, turning dish after 10 minutes.
Remove chicken to serving plate.
Cover to keep warm.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Add to liquid in baking dish.
Cook uncovered at High for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Mix sauce and chicken and serve. Makes 4 servings.
Contains approximately 139 calories per serving.

title: irish soda bread
directions: *Do not use self-rising flour.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Mix until it looks and tastes right!

title: yummy tuna casserole
directions: Cook pasta in 4 cups boiling water with oil.
In a 10 x 13-inch
pan,
combine
soup,
cream
cheese, tuna, onions and frozen vegetables.	Add
pasta
and blend well.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with parsley and paprika.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued meat sandwich
directions: Fully cook meat (leftover meat from roast is best).
In saucepan, stir in all sauce ingredients until hot.
Add meat and serve on buns with mayonnaise (potato rolls are best).

title: zarda(sweet saffron rice)
directions: Boil rice with a pinch of turmeric until well cooked, making sure that no hard kernel is left in rice.
Drain in colander. Prepare a syrup using the water, sugar and saffron.

title: aunt bea's tomato soup
directions: Heat tomatoes to boil, add soda and milk.
Season with butter, salt and pepper.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems from mushrooms.
Finely chop enough stems to measure 1/3 cup.
Cook and stir chopped mushroom stems, onion and green pepper in 3 tablespoons margarine until tender, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in bread crumbs, salt, thyme, turmeric and pepper.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak overnight in water the cucumbers, onions, peppers and 1/2 cup salt.
Drain.
Bring to a boil, then put cucumbers in the water and boil again, then put in jars.

title: pizza bites
directions: Mix margarine and garlic; spread on muffin halves.
Cut each muffin half into 4 wedges; do not separate.
Place 1 slice pepperoni and 1 tomato half on each muffin wedge.
Place in broiler pan.
Mix cheese and oregano; sprinkle over muffin wedges. Set oven control to broil.
Broil muffin wedges with tops about 5 inches from heat until cheese is melted, about 2 minutes.
Cut to separate into wedges.
Makes 6 servings, 65 calories per serving.

title: sin
directions: Whip and spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Serves 10.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in buttered baking dish.
Add water and cinnamon.
Work other ingredients together until crumbly and spread over the apple mixture.
Bake uncovered in moderate oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or plain cream.

title: festive fruit trifle
directions: Thaw berries, 1 package separately.
Drain peaches.
Cut pound cake lengthwise in half.
Cut each half crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Prepare vanilla pudding as directed, using only 2 1/2 cups milk.
Add almond extract.
Fold in 2 cups Cool Whip until blended.
Add juice from 1 package berries to orange juice.

title: chunky apple pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients and beat 30 seconds.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 55 minutes.

title: quickie apple dessert
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add beaten eggs.
Stir in apples. Combine flour, salt, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to apple mixture and mix well.
Pour into lightly greased glass pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or with sauce.

title: congo squares
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares when nearly cool.

title: rigatoni
directions: Boil above ingredients.
Brown ground hamburg; add to sauce. Cook.
Cook rigatoni noodles; drain.
Alternate layers with sauce in baking dish.
Put Mozzarella cheese throughout.
Put white American cheese on top.
Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place ingredients in large bowl.

title: jif peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Jif, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg; beat just until blended. Combine flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly in a criss-cross pattern with tines of fork.
Bake at 375° for 7-8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Put in a 1 1/2-quart glass pan the almond bark, milk chocolate chips and dark chocolate chips or semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Melt in microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes.
Add salted dry roasted peanuts to the chocolate mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls or tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.
Makes a large batch (about 60).
Half a recipe may be made.
Simple and delicious!

title: egg custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Scald the milk and oleo.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla together.
Add scalded milk (do not boil). Mix well.
Pour into pie crust shell.
Then put crust in oven and pour filling in.
Bake for 5 minutes at 475°.
Reduce heat and bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Remove from oven and cool.
Pie will be shaky, but will set as it cools.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: With cream cheese at room temperature, beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in sweetened condensed milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; beat well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop with a spoon on greased tin and bake in a moderate oven.

title: veggie casserole(fast!)
directions: Microwave veggies until they are almost done.
Add the soup; stir together.
Place in casserole dish; sprinkle cheese in and stir.
Sprinkle onion rings over top.
Bake at 400° until hot through and cheese is melted, about 30 minutes.

title: cheap but good chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk, flour, soda, salt and cocoa that has been dissolved in warm water. Add vanilla.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° about 25 minutes. Don't overbake.

title: easy chicken and rice bake
directions: Flour and brown chicken.
Put rice, salt and pepper in casserole.
Add onion and mushrooms.
Place chicken pieces on top. Pour bouillon over all.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut custard angel food cake
directions: Bake Lemon Custard Angel Food Cake as directed.
Frost top and sides with cooled vanilla pudding (cooked type).
Sprinkle toasted coconut over top and sides.
Chill before serving.

title: charlotte's vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all other ingredients together and place in crock-pot or in heavy saucepan and simmer for a couple of hours.
(Can use other vegetables of your choice and even more tomatoes if desired.)
This recipe is very easy and delicious!

title: browned rice(delicious rice dish, guaranteed to please company.)
directions: Bring margarine, bouillon and water to a boil in large skillet.
Add rice.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes, or until done.
Remove from stove.
Add 5 tablespoons soy sauce.
Cut up green onions and onion tops.
Add onions and nuts to taste. Serve.

title: stuffing
directions: For this versatile stuffing recipe, use day-old bread. Stuffing made with soft, fresh bread becomes mushy with cooking. If you have only fresh bread on hand, place slices in a 150° oven for a few minutes until dried throughout.

title: overnight walnut cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, shortening and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into long rolls.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Slice about 1/2-inch thick and bake at 325° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: delicious biscuits
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder, cream of tartar, salt and
sugar.
Cut
in
shortening.
I slowly pour in milk; add eggs.
Bake in hot oven for 10 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook meat in large iron pot.
Remove and drain all but 2 tablespoons of grease.
Add chopped onions, bell pepper, garlic and celery.
Cook until soft.
Add spices, tomatoes, rice and beer. Add meat and then enough water to cover rice, about 1-inch.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Cook until rice is done, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, allspice and cloves; set aside.
Combine oil and sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Beginning and ending with dry ingredients, add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce to sugar mixture.
Fold in nuts, raisins and coconut.
Pour in a greased 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes on a rack.

title: meat loaf surprise
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack half of mixture in an ungreased loaf pan, forming a trench in the middle.
Fill the trench with your favorite bread stuffing and cover with the remaining meat. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, add diced onion.
Cook until transparent.
In large pot add tomato juice, tomato paste, chili powder, cold water, salt sugar, worcestershire sauce, kidney beans and browned hamburger onion mix.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
(Can be frozen.)

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in bananas. Combine dry ingredients and mix in undrained pineapple and coconut.
Bake in 2 large or 3 medium loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
This freezes well.

title: cry babies
directions: Boil sugar, molasses and raisins until raisins are plump.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: spiced fruit cider
directions: Bring to a boil.
Simmer.
Strain spices and serve warm.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Place croutons in greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Cook sausage in skillet and drain.
Then place sausage over cheese. Beat eggs and mix with mustard, milk, soup and mushrooms.
Pour over sausage and bake in preheated oven at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Best if prepared and refrigerated overnight.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Bring oil, sugar, vinegar, pepper, salt and mustard to a boil. Reduce heat and add eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Blend in salad dressing or mayonnaise.

title: chipped beef and spread
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix together with all ingredients, except pecans.
Put in casserole dish; top with pecan halves.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Serve as a spread for crackers.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, brown meat with onion.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter popcorn balls
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in small saucepan.
Heat to boiling; stir until sugar dissolves.
Remove.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over popped corn.
Mix until coated.
Shape into balls with greased hands.
Makes 10 balls.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and combine in large bowl with butter; add salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend thoroughly and pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with melted butter and flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix everything and spread on chicken.
Bake in oven at 350° to 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Mix all in a crock-pot.
Cook 4 to 6 hours.
Start on high, then low.
Stir occasionally.

title: jello pound cake
directions: Mix jello in boiling water. Let cool.
Mix cake mix, jello mixture, oil and 4 eggs.
Beat 5 minutes.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350° or until done. Leave cake in pan and cover with powdered sugar.
Mix together orange juice and sugar.
Pour over cake while hot.
Let stand in pan until cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix the broccoli, cauliflower, onion, carrots, ripe olives and cherry tomatoes in a large bowl.
Pour on salad dressing and chill.
Cook pasta according to directions; drain well.
Mix with vegetables; sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: sweet minglers
directions: Open a large Ziploc Baggie and place on counter. Place a sifter securely in Baggie. Measure the powdered sugar into the sifter. Sift and set aside.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together hamburger, bread crumbs, milk, egg, soup mix, salt and nutmeg.
Shape into balls.
Cook in glass Pyrex baking dish.
Cook 20 meatballs at a time.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Rearrange after 3 minutes. Remove, keep drippings in the pan.
Repeat until all meatballs are cooked.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into a prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 6 ounce package butterscotch morsels. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to cream mixture.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate and Reese's chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing cookies. Makes 5 dozen 2 1/2 inch cookies.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Cut the meat off the bones and store in the refrigerator until you are ready.
Combine the seasonings (next 6 ingredients) in a small bowl and set aside.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate and serve chilled.

title: divinity candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and corn syrup until it spins a thread. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly pour syrup over egg whites. Beat until egg whites stand in peaks.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat until it thickens.
Drop candy onto waxed paper by spoonfuls.

title: corn bread
directions: Stir together the flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, milk and oil or melted shortening.
Beat just until smooth (do not overbeat).
Turn into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 8 or 9 servings.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into dish.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix soup-spaghetti mix in hamburger.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 package crescent rolls. Add layer of hamburger mixture and layer of cheese.
Top with other package of crescent rolls.
Brush top with milk.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until rolls are brown.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix well the pineapple juice, milk and lemon juice, then fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: onion wine soup
directions: Saute onions and add beef broth and celery leaves.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Puree mixture in blender.
Return mixture to saucepan and blend in wine, vinegar and sugar.
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Stir in cream, parsley, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: 24 hour cold slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, celery seed and sugar.
Set aside. Combine vinegar, salt and dry mustard in saucepan.
Bring to boil, then add vegetable oil and bring to boil again.
Pour liquid over cabbage ingredients.
Pack lightly and cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Will keep for 7 to 8 days if kept refrigerated.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Put sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Shake.
Shake biscuit pieces a few at a time in cinnamon mixture.
Layer them in a well greased bundt pan. Sprinkle raisins and nuts over each biscuit layer.
Top with nuts and raisins.
Melt brown sugar and butter.
Boil for one minute. Add vanilla.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 35 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Pull apart with a fork.

title: quick yeast bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix together the water, yeast, sugar, shortening and salt.
Gradually stir in the flour until thoroughly mixed.
Cover this bowl; let mixture rise for 30 to 45 minutes. Punch down and shape into rolls with floured hands, or put in a greased loaf pan and let rise until doubles in bulk.
Bake at 425°.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp; drain.
Add all ingredients and mix well.

title: vietnamese fried rice
directions: In large skillet add first 7 ingredients.
Stir-fry until tender and hot.
Mix in meat.
Add rice and stir-fry 5 minutes. Add vegetables, stirring well.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and dark molasses.
Mix well and add ginger, cinnamon, baking soda and flour.
Chill and roll in ball about the size of a walnut.
Then roll in granulated sugar. Put on ungreased cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: marty's almost chinese vegetables
directions: Place tomatoes in large saucepan.
Break up tomatoes with side of spoon.
Add drained green beans, bean sprouts and mushrooms. Add Mrs. Dash to taste and heat over medium fire until hot.
Serve immediately.

title: mustard and applesauce chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Skin chicken; coat with mixture of mustard and sugar.
Place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Spread applesauce over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg and pat into greased 9x 12-inch pan.
Cream the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar and pour into pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle a little powdered sugar on top after baking.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Beat until light.
Whip sour cream and fold into egg mixture.
Add raisins, nutmeg, salt and lemon juice. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for another 20 minutes or until filling is set and tests done with toothpick.

title: crab a la lorraine
directions: Blend ingredients well. Spread on 16 muffin halves. Freeze slightly and cut each into 6 wedges. Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: glennie nell's roast christmas possum
directions: Combine one food from each of the groups below:

title: gumdrop hermits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut gumdrops into small pieces, totaling 1 cup.
Use ice water to dip knife to prevent sticking. Cream shortening; gradually add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk and egg.
Add gumdrops and vanilla.
Drop with teaspoon on greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown on bottom.

title: cathy's champagne punch
directions: Combine in large punch bowl; serve.

title: melon-strawberry compote
directions: Combine semi-defrosted melon and strawberries.
Pour lemon-lime soda over and lightly toss.
Spoon into eight sherbet glasses and garnish with fresh mint leaves.
Makes 8 servings.

title: honey dijon chicken
directions: Dip chicken breast halves in salad dressing, coating well. Combine bread crumbs and cheese, then coat chicken with crumb mixture.
Place on a nonstick pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: banana chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Mix rest of ingredients and bake in a 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch square pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onions, parsley, celery, carrots and turnips with salt and water.
Bring to boil and cook gently until potatoes are tender.
Cook on simmer, stir frequently and watch closely. Sticks to bottom of pot very easily.
Make a white sauce.

title: pastel banana bobs
directions: Peel bananas; cut crosswise into 4 pieces.
Insert wooden ice cream stick in each piece.
Place on baking sheet.
Freeze until bananas are firm, about 2 hours.

title: country biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Mix in buttermilk. Roll out and cut to desired thickness.
Place in greased pan (bacon grease gives it a great flavor).
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Blend cornstarch and cold water in a saucepan.
Add boiling water and cook, stirring, until clear and thickened. Let stand until completely cold.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Set oven to 425°.
Wash blueberries; drain.
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry and flute edge.
Combine vinegar, sugar, flour and nutmeg with berries.
Turn into pastry shell and dot with butter. Cover with pastry.
Seal edge.
Bake pie 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 25 minutes longer.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil sugar and molasses together for 5 minutes (not any longer); remove from heat.
Add butter and baking soda.
Stir mixture until it becomes foamy.
Pour over the popcorn.
Mix well. Wet hands with cold water and shape into balls.

title: orange pumpkin cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir in pumpkin and orange peel.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and allspice.
Add to mixture in bowl.
Add orange juice and nuts.
Pour into 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar on top, if desired.

title: rice with black beans
directions: Cook and stir onion in hot oil in saucepan until tender, but not browned.
Add tomatoes, beans, oregano and garlic powder. Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 8 servings.
One serving equals 170 calories, 7 g protein, 32 g carbohydrate, 3 g fat, 0 cholesterol, 340 mg sodium and 4 g dietary fiber.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter in 1-quart saucepan. Add onion and cook until tender.
Add salt, pepper and flour; blend well.
Add parsley, celery, potatoes and water.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and place over high heat about 5 minutes.
Reduce to low and cook 15 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Add milk and heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: paul's fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except jello.
Sprinkle jello over mixture; stir, then chill for several hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Flatten the cookie roll into a 12-inch pizza pan. Punch holes in crust before baking. Bake at 325° until brown (about 7 minutes).

title: smash-um-forget-um cookies
directions: Preheat oven. 350°. Mix together above ingredients. Roll into balls. Squash on cookie sheet. Put in oven. Turn OFF oven. Leave cookies for 5 min.

title: pork chops-barbecued
directions: Brown chops lightly in very little oil.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chops and bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Stir in cooled, melted chocolate. Add eggs, one at a time, beating at high speed 5 minutes after each addition.
Fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Pour in pie shell. Chill until firm, 2 hours.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Put potatoes in mixing bowl and add eggs.
Mix well. Gradually beat in sugar; stir in milk, butter, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°
until light brown and well set.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Fry hamburger, pepper and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low heat 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream nut pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix to dissolve and pour over hot cake. (I punch holes in the cake before pouring mixture over cake.)

title: mandle cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in blender.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients which have been mixed together. Add extract and blend thoroughly.
Separate dough into four even amounts.
Drop food coloring in desired amounts. Put through cookie press onto ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter, syrup and vanilla.
Add to beaten eggs, then add pecans.
Pour into pie pan lined with good rich pastry shell (unbaked).
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in casserole dish. Top with mayonnaise. Grate cheese of your choice on top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook the cranberries with the 1 1/2 cups water and sugar until thick.
Let cool.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over the Jell-O; let it cool.
Add drained pineapple, celery, apples and nuts to Jell-O.
Mix well.
Add the cooked cranberries.
Put into large dish and refrigerate.
This salad will keep for several days.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend together all ingredients.
Pour mixture into pie shell (9-inch).
Bake at 375° until sharp bladed knife inserted near center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes. Cool.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook beef until tender, then shred or chop beef.
Put back into liquid and add all seasonings.
Cook on low all day.
Stir once or twice.

title: brownie dessert
directions: Prepare brownie mix and mousse according to package directions.
Layer in clear bowl a layer of brownies (optional: pour Kahlua over brownies), a layer of mousse and a layer of Cool Whip; sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Repeat until you reach the top of bowl.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Over medium heat, in large saucepan, melt margarine and cheese.
Spread, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth. Blend powdered sugar and cocoa into cheese mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and spread into buttered pan, depending on thickness you want, 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 15 x 11-inch.
Yields 6 1/2 pounds.

title: dairy queen ice cream
directions: Soak the Knox gelatine in the cold water.
Heat the whole milk until hot, but not boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add the gelatine, vanilla, sugar and salt.
Cool.
Add the whipping cream.
Put in refrigerator to chill for 5 or 6 hours before freezing.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let set overnight in refrigerator. Next morning, add bananas and nuts.
Mix well.

title: barbecued hot dogs
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add onion and celery.
Cook until yellow. Add remaining ingredients and blend. Cook slowly for about 15 minutes.
Put the hot dogs in a flat baking dish.
Prick them with a fork. Pour sauce over them and bake for about 20 minutes until bubbly in a 350° oven.
Bake uncovered.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly. Pack firmly into loaf pan. Top with 1 can mushroom soup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing. Yields 8 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together except for 1/2 of the cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top with rest of cheese near end of baking time.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Lightly brown chicken in butter. Remove chicken.
Place mushrooms, soy sauce and tarragon in butter.
Saute.
Add whipping cream. Stir.
Add chicken.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Do not overcook.

title: dottie's almond bark candy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Turn off.
Put bark in glass dish and melt in oven.
Mix all ingredients together, making sure it's mixed well.
Drop on cookie sheets lined with wax paper by the teaspoon.
Put in the refrigerator until hard.
(They harden quickly.)
Layer in tin can with wax paper between layers.

title: old fashioned irish stew
directions: Have the meat cut in pieces as desired for serving size.
Cover with about 4 cups water (boiling); bring slowly back to boiling point.
Add the seasonings.
Add the carrots, cut in strips or thick slices; let simmer for 45 minutes.
Add onions and potatoes; let simmer until potatoes and meat are both tender, about 1 hour. Garnish with chopped parsley when serving.
To be served with a salad and a dessert of shamrock ice cream molds and little cookies.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli according to package; add a little butter. Add Minute rice to mixture; cover for 3 minutes.
Pour Cheese Spread over mixture for serving.

title: german rye bread(if you like dark rye bread, this is the recipe for you.)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup water.
Mix rest of water with molasses and salt in a large bowl.
Mix rye flour, cocoa and caraway seed together.
Add yeast and melted butter and 1/2 of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Knead in remaining flour until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down.
Shape into loaves and let rise again until double.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken and broccoli dish
directions: Use a glass baking dish (spray with Pam).
Place broccoli on bottom of dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup and mayonnaise together.
Spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top of soup; sprinkle on bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: salad supreme
directions: Soak lime jello in cold water for 10 minutes.
Combine lemon juice from lemons, pineapple juice and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Add softened jello and let cool.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple.
When mixture starts to thicken, add whipped cream. Beat well.
Serve on crisp lettuce with mayonnaise, chopped nuts and paprika.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine parsley, mayonnaise, mustard, cayenne, salt and Worcestershire; mix well.
Stir in crumbs and egg.
Add crab meat; mix well.
Shape into patties; refrigerate 1 hour.
Melt butter or oleo in skillet; saute cakes until golden brown on both sides.

title: hollandaise sauce (france)
directions: Into a blender, place yolks, salt, mustard, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce.
Blend for 3 seconds.
Then, while blender is going, pour in the melted butter, which should be hot.
(The temperature of the butter is the secret; make it very hot without burning it, and the Hollandaise Sauce will thicken immediately.) Serve on vegetables, poached eggs (Eggs Benedict) or meats.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage together; drain.
Put back in skillet.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Melt cheese on low and stir.
Put heaping spoonful of mixture on party bread and spread. Place on cookie sheet and bake now or freeze.

title: carol's chicken casserole
directions: Pour Pet milk over noodles and let stand while preparing. Cube the cheese.
Mix together everything except potato chips. Add chips to the top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
A family favorite - and great to bring to shut-ins!

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all of this together and place in a 9 x 11 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top (I use Italian cheese seasoned).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread crumbs are lightly browned.

title: apricot delight
directions: Pour into saucepan pineapple, water and gelatin.
Let come to a ripple.
Add cream cheese; stir until cream cheese is almost dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Pour into a mixing bowl and set in the refrigerator for about 15 or 20 minutes.
Whip the Dream Whip and add to the cooled pineapple mixture.
Add nuts and celery. Pour into mold.
Best if chilled overnight.

title: pudding cake
directions: Layer 1:
Cut butter into flour until crumbly.	Stir in nuts. Pat down
firmly.
Bake
in 13 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: honey pecan fried chicken
directions: Place chicken in marinating dish and cover with buttermilk. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Do not rinse the buttermilk off the chicken. Combine flour, garlic salt and cayenne pepper in large bowl. Dredge chicken in flour mixture and allow to sit at room temperature for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb with 1/4 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar until it can be mashed.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add all ingredients to jello.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.

title: meal in one
directions: You will need foil.

title: sweet and sour
directions: In a 1-cup measuring cup, add enough water to reserved juice to measure full cup.
In medium saucepan, heat juice and water, adding brown sugar, vinegar, carrots, soy sauce and salt.
Stir. Add garlic; bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 6 minutes.
Mix water and cornstarch; stir into sauce.
Add pineapple, your choice of meat and green pepper.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: hamburger-macaroni
directions: Brown burger in heavy pan. Add onion, soup, milk and salt and pepper.
Cook about 30 minutes. Stir every 10 minutes.
Add cheese.
Turn off burner.
Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain well and pour in bowl. Add sauce.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water. In mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter, salt and milk. Cool to lukewarm. Stir in egg and yeast. Gradually add flour to form a stiff dough.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Dissolve cornmeal in milk in a saucepan.
Stir over heat to scalding point.
Simmer until thickened.
Add salt, stir in sugar, butter, corn, chilies and cheese.
Allow to cool a few minutes. Add eggs and baking powder.
Pour into greased two-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until top is puffy and brown, approximately 10 servings.

title: orange-oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine first four ingredients, mixing until crumbly.
Set aside.
Combine next seven ingredients in a medium mixing bowl, stirring well.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine orange juice, milk, oil and egg.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Spoon mixture into greased muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: yogurt waffles
directions: Mix together eggs, yogurt and oil.
Add flour, soda and salt. Mix together until smooth.
Add water, adding additional water if necessary to make the right consistency for your waffle iron. Makes 2 1/2 large waffles.

title: chicken breasts in lemon sauce
directions: Dredge chicken breast with flour, salt and pepper.
Place in skillet in which butter has been melted and garlic sauteed.
Brown on both sides.
Add wine and lemon juice.
Cook 5 minutes or until done.

title: coffee cream pie filling and crust
directions: Combine and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until melted, the coffee, water and miniature marshmallows.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add coffee mixture slowly to beaten egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Return to saucepan; cook over medium heat for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Chill until mixture begins to set like soft pudding.
Beat chilled mixture at medium speed until smooth.
Fold in with beater the whipped topping and almond extract.
If too stiff, add some whole milk until smooth. Spoon into cooled crusts.
Garnish with dry instant coffee crystals.

title: easy baked pork chops
directions: Wash and dry chops.
Place in baking dish.
Mix catsup and water.
Pour over chops (may need more if using more chops.) Place 1 teaspoon brown sugar on each chop with 1 lemon slice on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until chops are done.
These are delicious and very easy to prepare.
tags: thin slice lemon per pork chop

title: french cherry pie
directions: Beat sour cream and milk with beater until smooth.
Add vanilla pudding mix and almond extract; beat 1 minute.
Pour into pie shell; chill 15 minutes.
Spread pie filling evenly over pudding.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: country pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pat in 10-inch pie plate.

title: easy banana nut bread
directions: Mix thoroughly after each addition.
Turn into well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Check doneness by inserting toothpick.
When it comes out clean, it's done!

title: baked broccoli spears
directions: Boil broccoli 5 minutes.
Strain well. Beat eggs, cheese, soup and mayonnaise together. Fold into the broccoli.
Pack them in greased casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, saving out some cheese for top.
Spread in large 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Add cheese to top of casserole during last 15 minutes of baking.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in halves and place cream side up.
Pour crushed pineapple and juice over Twinkies.
Cut up bananas on crushed pineapple.
Cover pineapple with thawed Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: baked peaches
directions: Place peaches in lightly greased pie baking dish. Combine dry ingredients. Cut in margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over peaches. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar slowly and mix well.
Beat in egg yolks.
Sift flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk and honey mixture.
Beat well.
Add raisins and figs which have been coated with flour.
