Fold in egg whites which have been beaten stiff.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° in a well-greased tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Two cups brown sugar, one cup milk and butter size of walnut. Stir while cooking.
Boil 20 minutes, then add flavoring and a cup of chopped nuts.
Beat until creamy and spread on buttered tin to cool.

title: scotch cookies
directions: Thoroughly combine sugar and butter.
Add molasses and eggs. Combine dry ingredients and add gradually to butter mixture.
Roll out on lightly floured board, and cut with large cookie cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and brush with topping.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, mushrooms and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Add margarine to spaghetti; toss to melt margarine.
Place half of the spaghetti with half the meat mixture; repeat layers.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until bubbling around edge.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cooked frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick; stir while cooking.
Beat sugar, butter, Crisco and vanilla until fluffy like whipped cream. Add to cooled flour mixture and beat until all sugar is dissolved and looks fluffy.
Will store 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator.
Just whip again before use.
Great on chocolate cake!

title: potato chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottoms of 2 (9-inch) layer pans or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan with waxed paper cut to fit.
Prepare mashed potatoes.
(Easy way is to follow directions for 2 servings on package mashed potatoes.) Measure and set aside.
Gradually beat sugar into shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla and potatoes.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately, about 1/4 of each at a time, beating smooth.
Stir in walnuts.

title: zucchini jack casserole
directions: Slice zucchini into 1/4-inch thick rounds (about 7 cups); set aside.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with milk, baking powder and flour until smooth.
Stir in parsley, garlic, onion, chiles, cheese and zucchini.
Spoon egg mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Toss croutons in melted butter, then sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand at least 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Drain water chestnuts.
Cut bacon slices into thirds.
Wrap each water chestnut in 1/3 slice of bacon.
Place two on a toothpick.
Continue with remaining water chestnuts and bacon. (Tedious!
But can be done a day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.) Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain grease and discard. While these are in the oven, combine remaining ingredients.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour sauce over drained water chestnuts.
Return to oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
These are wonderful hot appetizers!

title: white punch
directions: Boil water; add sugar.
Blend bananas, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Add this to the water/sugar mixture.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, add 2-quarts ginger ale.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Spread on platter.
Cover with taco layer.
Layer chopped vegetables on top of cheese and taco sauce.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Serve with restaurant style tortilla chips.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and peppers; mix and pour 1/2 into greased pan.
Spread peppers over batter; sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Cover with remaining batter.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple orange cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 6 quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot.
May garnish with cinnamon sticks if desired.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in greased, 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
In mixing bowl, cream together margarine and sugar.
Stir in flour.
Add egg and vanilla and mix well.
Spoon mixture over peaches.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add Pet milk; cook until it thickens slightly.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Place in freezer.
Finish filling up freezer with milk (3/4 full).
Freeze until hard.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Saute onion in part of the butter.
Mix rest of ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add onion.
Place in casserole and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Put corn flakes on top and drizzle rest of butter and additional cheese, if desired.
Bake 15 more minutes.

title: taffy
directions: Boil until brittle when dropped into cold water. When cool, pull.

title: chocolate delight
directions: For first layer, melt oleo and mix with flour and 1/2 cup pecans.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate 1 hour then add second layer.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine meat, egg and cracker crumbs.
Mix well and form into loafs and place in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Bake at 450° for 1/2 hour, baste with sauce and bake 1 more hour at 350°.

title: salmon cheddar pie
directions: Very lightly mix the salmon, Cheddar cheese, eggs and seasonings in mixing bowl.
Pour equal amounts in each pie shell. Bake in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm. Serve with dollop of sour cream and fresh fruit.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool.
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish and chill until firm.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Combine apples, walnuts, raisins, honey and cinnamon.
Divide ingredients between squash halves.
Dot with butter.
Bake in a pan of water at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake another 30 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburgers, arkansas style
directions: Mix and let stand 1/2 hour.
Spread on buns without packing, covering edges of buns well.
Broil until done.

title: mike's own baked spaghetti
directions: Boil ground chuck until cooked.
Mix tomato sauce, chili mix, sugar, salt and pepper.
After ground chuck is done, drain and add to tomato sauce mixture.
Simmer for about 45 minutes.
Boil noodles until done.
(Try to get noodles and sauce done at the same time.)

title: red raspberry ring
directions: Drain raspberries, reserving liquid.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add ice cream by spoonfuls and stir until blended. Stir in raspberry syrup and lemonade concentrate.
Chill until partially set; add pecans and raspberries.
Turn into 6-cup mold; chill until firm.

title: the "ultimate" chocolate chip cookie
directions: Combine butter flavored shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.

Beat at medium speed on electric mixer until creamy. Beat egg into creamed mixture. Combine flour, salt and baking soda and mix into creamed mixture until just blended. Stir in chocolate chips (and nuts, if you're using them).

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Grease a pie dish and fill with apples. Mix cinnamon and 3 tablespoons of sugar together.
Sprinkle over apples.
Beat the 3/4 cup sugar and butter until creamy.
Add salt and baking powder.
Mix in egg, flour and nuts. Mix together thoroughly. Drop the batter by tablespoons over the top of apples. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pie(strawberries are so good in a pie.)
directions: In a small bowl, mix cream cheese with milk.
Spread into a baked pie shell.
Wash and stem whole strawberries, then place in pie shell, covering shell.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Blend
ingredients
in
large
mixing
bowl with mixer. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes one 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: "ms. louella's" peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together and make into little balls. Place on cookie sheet and flatten a little with a fork dipped in water. Bake in slow oven, 250° to 275°, until done (8 to 9 minutes depending on cookie sheet and oven).

title: thrifty pound cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Sift flour once, measure and add baking powder.
Sift again.
Put shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring in a large bowl of an electric mixer.
On high speed, beat 2 1/2 to 3 minutes; then turn to low.
Mix milk and flour, alternately, about 1/3 cup milk and flour at a time.
Just mix long enough to get mixed good.
Bake in a well greased and floured tube pan for an hour at 350°.

title: baked bean special
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add remaining ingredients mixing well. Place in a 3-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 10.

title: beef and macaroni
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off grease.
Put in Miracle Whip, spaghetti sauce and cooked macaroni.
Heat on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add cut up cabbage.
Bake in a large, greased pan or baking dish at 350°, covered, for 2 hours.

title: refrigerator mustard pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into quarters and keep in jar in refrigerator.

title: dill weed vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate for awhile before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces; combine with other ingredients.
Stir well.
This salad is best if prepared and refrigerated at least 3 or 4 hours before serving.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese and milk until smooth. Stir in Hidden Valley Ranch dressing mix and dill weed.
Chill and serve with your favorite vegetable.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar, vinegar and spices together and mix until well blended in crock-pot.
Turn on high and cover.
After 4 hours, remove lid and finish cooking until thick enough to spread. Cook 8 to 10 hours.

title: chicken balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well; shape into 1-inch balls.
Fry in a small amount of hot oil over medium heat until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Tie whole cloves in cheesecloth and set aside.
Combine 1/3 cup brown sugar and cornstarch in a large saucepan.
Gradually add water, stirring until smooth.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice; cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Add meatballs and whole cloves.
Simmer on low 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove cheesecloth bag.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: grandma haynes' biscuits
directions: Mix 1/5 can lye in 6 cups cold water and dissolve in enamel pan.
Put 1 pound lard or other grease into lye water and boil until fairly thick (like candy); add 2 tablespoons ammonia water and 1 tablespoon borax; when cool, beat well until white.
Harden 2 weeks before using.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Blend all together and let stand.

title: momma's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with well beaten eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and sour cream; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan and bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in top of double boiler.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Add chopped cherries, raisins and pecans. Pour 2 tablespoons cherry juice over mixture and press back in cracker box.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Wash and bake potatoes.
Melt oleo. Stir in	milk.
Remove
from
heat.
Add
soup.	Take potatoes from shell
and	beat
in milk mixture.	Put filling back into shells and bake until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ribbon jello
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to 1 package of Jell-O; let dissolve. Take half the Jell-O (1/2 cup) and add 3 tablespoons of cold water; pour into a 9 x 13 dish.
Let set.
To the other 1/2 cup of Jell-O, add 1/3 cup sour cream and shake until smooth.
Scoop foam off sour cream and Jell-O.
Mix and pour.
Let set.
Keep doing same with each layer.

title: quick cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix juice and tapioca and let set 15 minutes. In a large pan, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Place 1/2 mixture in bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer cherries on top of this layer.
Pour on cherry juice and tapioca mixture.
Top with remaining sugar and oatmeal mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: apricot chews
directions: Mix together; stir well.
Drop on well greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Freezes well.
Serve as candy or cookie.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: Melt margarine over low heat using a large pan (or microwave). Add marshmallows and stir until all are melted.
Add peanut butter.
Pour whole mixture over the popcorn.
Stir until well coated.
Form into balls with greased hands.
Can also use plastic bags on hands to form balls.
Makes 15 balls.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix and set aside chopped nuts, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and cocoa.
Cream margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs and sour cream. Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt and mix.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Put 1/2 batter into tube pan, then add 1/2 cinnamon mixture on top and cut through with knife. Add rest of batter and then rest of cinnamon.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: frozen banana smoothie
directions: In blender container, place all ingredients.
Cover; blend on high speed 2 minutes.
Decrease speed; blend 1 minute longer or until frothy.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: mom's mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and boil in water enough to cover potatoes. Boil until potatoes are tender to touch. Drain off water and add butter, milk, salt and pepper. Let set long enough for butter to melt. With mixer, beat potatoes until light and fluffy. If potatoes seem too stiff, add a little milk and stir.

title: peach coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together butter, flour, baking powder, vanilla, eggs and 2 cups sugar.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a large greased cake pan and spread evenly.
Cover this with a mixture of the peaches, cinnamon and the remaining sugar.
Pour the remaining batter over this.
Bake for 50 minutes.
If you like walnuts, mix in 1 cup to the batter.

title: cookies and cream dessert
directions: Pour crushed cookies in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over crushed cookies.
Place in refrigerator and serve next day.
Optional:
Top with Cool Whip and extra crushed Oreos.

title: chitterlings
directions: Wash chitterlings.
Pull off all excess fat.
Split open chitterlings and clean thoroughly.
Wash in several waters.

title: low-fat fudgy brownies(yields 25 brownies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick coating and set aside.
Combine all ingredients except flour and walnuts in bowl and beat to blend with electric mixer on low.
Stir in flour and spoon into pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if using.
Bake for 30 minutes or until center springs back when gently touched with tip of finger.
Cool brownies in pan or wire rack.
Cut into squares.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat into cakes.
Fry or bake.

title: cherry-o cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat softened cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually mix in sweetened condensed milk until thoroughly blended.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Turn into crust. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Top with chilled pie filling.

title: welsh rarebit
directions: Cut up cheese and add water.
Heat in a saucepan until cheese melts.
Add butter, salt and flour, which has been thickened with a little water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over saltine crackers.

title: chili popcorn seasoning
directions: Add all ingredients into a shaker type dispenser and mix well. Shake container several times before sprinkling over warm popcorn.

title: basic quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese and meat into pie shell.
Beat the remaining ingredients.
Pour over cheese and meat.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: german raisin pie
directions: Crust:
Crumble enough pecan sandies for pie crust.
Blend these with just enough butter to hold crumbs together.
Press this mixture into an 8-inch pie pan.
Set aside.

title: lynn's bean dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Drain grease off.
Add all other ingredients.
Heat and mix thoroughly.
Serve with taco chips. Great in small crock pot for parties.

title: spam hash brown bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine potatoes, melted butter, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
In another bowl, combine cheese, Spam, soup, sour cream, milk, onion and green chilies. Mix well.
Add Spam mixture to potato mixture; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 8.

title: yummy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat together margarine and sugar until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well. Stir in oats and raisins; mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet. Remove to wire rack. Makes approximately 4 dozen cookies. Makes 30 servings. Preparation time: 0:35.

title: cherry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Add a few spoons of Cool Whip so you can spread it onto crust easier.
Spread pie filling on top of cream cheese, then cover with Cool Whip.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: family noodles alfredo
directions: Cook noodles to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain and rinse under hot water.
Combine butter and milk in large saucepan.
Heat until butter melts.
Stir in cooked noodles, stirring gently, until heated through.
Remove from heat.
Toss with Parmesan cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle lightly with parsley flakes on top of noodles.

title: marshmallow lime chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Combine egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Stir over very low heat until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat; blend in gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat 2 egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually beat in 1/3 cup sugar.
Fold in 2 cups miniature marshmallows. Pour in baked pie shell.
Sprinkle on top 1/2 cup flaked coconut.

title: spam potato bake
directions: In shallow baking dish, prepare potatoes according to directions on box.
Cube Spam and add to mix.
Stir in green beans.
Bake according to box directions.

title: chicken salad(easy to make - an all-american favorite)
directions: Toss together chicken, celery, lemon juice and seasonings. Mix in mayonnaise.
Carefully fold in eggs.
Chill thoroughly. Arrange a mound in each lettuce cup and garnish with olives or little pickles and parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Add oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to apple mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch well greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Layer the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with Doritos.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over the layer of Doritos.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° uncovered until hot and the cheese is melted.

title: squash with apple filling
directions: Pierce squash with fork in several places and bake whole until they are soft but still firm.
Let cool until comfortable to handle.
Cut squash in half and scoop out seeds.
Fill squash cavity with apple pie filling and sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° until hot, about 20 minutes.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Place the jello in bowl with about 1 teaspoon chopped ginger. Pour boiling water over and stir.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then add the ginger ale.
Place in refrigerator until like maple syrup (about 45 to 60 minutes).
Place the grapes, grapefruit and orange in lightly oiled pan.
Sprinkle with about 1 teaspoon chopped ginger.
Lastly, pour jello over fruit and chill.
Serves 6.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice in 3 cups water and salt for 20 minutes.
Add cooked and drained spinach, onion, 1/3 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir in herbs and melted butter.
Put mixture in casserole dish and add eggs beaten with milk.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese, dot with butter and bake 1 1/4 hours.

title: mrs. carraway's fresh coconut cake(from the files of dessie bell hayes)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients with milk, water, vanilla and beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix all this together.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with rice.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Butter baking pan 7 x 11-inches.
Mix crumbs with melted butter.
Press into buttered pan.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips, then nuts, and then coconut.
Pour milk evenly over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cut when cold.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add milk and butter; cook for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Stir in oats and drop spoonfuls onto wax paper until set.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Use the juice and enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Heat and pour over gelatin, stirring until it is dissolved.
Slowly stir in buttermilk. Add pineapple, oranges, pecans and whipped topping. Chill.

title: sausage and cornbread pie
directions: Cook sausage, onion and garlic in a large skillet over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain.
Add tomatoes, chilies, corn and chili powder; simmer 20 minutes. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish; set aside.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Blend all spices with the flour.
Rub spice blend into boned, skinned breasts.
Let chicken sit at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Cut into pieces.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.

title: bacon & egg lasagna
directions: In a skillet, cook Bacon until crisp.
Remove with slotted spoon to paper towel.
Drain, reserving 1/3 c. drippings.
In drippings, saute Onion until tender.
Stir in Flour, Salt and Pepper until blended.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Spread 1/2 cup Sauce in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Layer with four Noodles, a third of the Egg, Bacon, Swiss Cheese and white sauce. Repeat layers twice.
Sprinkle with Parmesan Cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 for 35 - 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with Parsley.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: sausage and cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread cubes on bottom of flat baking dish. Beat eggs. Add milk, salt and dry mustard.
Place sausage and cheese over crumbs.
Pour milk and egg mixture over all.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Bake uncovered.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender. Take off of stove. Drain macaroni. Put in your cheese while hot. Turn stove on low to let cheese melt. Add your butter and milk and let all this melt together. It's very good.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix pecans and confectioners sugar well.
Add sifted flour and baking powder and continue to mix well.
Add teaspoons of vanilla. Add whites of eggs that have been stiffly beaten.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet and bake until slightly brown. Have your oven a little less than 250°.

title: angge's salad
directions: Combine condensed milk,
cherry pie filling and pineapple. Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill until set.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding Accent to taste.
Great with celery, carrot sticks, cucumbers, etc.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
Refrigerate.

title: ham and cheese flips
directions: Combine first four ingredients in small bowl, set aside. Separate biscuits and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press or roll each biscuit into a 5-inch circle.
Spoon 1/2 cup ham mixture onto half of biscuit.
Brush edges with water.
Fold dough over filling and press edges with fork to seal.
Make a 1-inch crescent shaped slit on top of each turnover.
Brush with milk.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 5 servings.

title: sarah barbre's school rolls(home recipe)
directions: Pour warm water in mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar.
Sprinkle yeast in and stir.
Add oil.
Mix flour, dry milk and salt together; add to mixture.
Beat well.
Let dough rest awhile, then roll out and cut.
Place on greased pan and let rise.
Bake at 450° until light brown.
Brush tops with butter.
This dough may be let rise only once because the yeast has been upped in it.
Rolls, buns, loaves, cinnamon rolls or doughnuts may all be made from this dough.

title: slushy lemonade
directions: In blender container, combine lemon juice, sugar and water. Add ice to make 4 cups.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses. Serve immediately.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and cover with sugar.
Let set several hours.
Mix Jell-O and boiling water and add other ingredients. Mix together with cranberries.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Add cucumber, onion, green pepper, vinegar, mayonnaise and cottage cheese; mix well.
Pour into serving bowl.
Chill until set.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: baked grits souffle
directions: Cook grits; add margarine, cheese, milk and egg yolks.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered, until set.
Can be prepared the day before and refrigerated until time to bake.

title: judy's potatoes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl, then add potatoes.
Mix.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with melted margarine mixed with crumbled corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Freezes well.)

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Put the Twinkies into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare the pudding mix with 2 cups milk.
Pour over Twinkies. Cover with the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle the Heath bars over top and refrigerate.

title: giovanni peppers
directions: *More sweet than hot, but do to suit own taste.

title: crust baked chicken
directions: Coat an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Heat oven to 375°.
Beat whites, chili powder, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Place bread crumbs on plate.
Dip chicken in egg.
Coat with crumbs.
Place in baking dish.
Oven bake for 25 to 30 minutes. Contains 156 calories; 1 gram fat; 470 sodium and 13 mg cholesterol.

title: grandma's hot dish
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add soup, water and chow mein noodles. Stir all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour or less.

title: greek salad for two
directions: In large bowl, mix both lettuces and two cheeses.
Place on salad plates and arrange vegetables so they look nice.
Pour dressing over and serve with croutons.

title: pieroghi
directions: Potato Filling:
Boil potatoes and mash.
Add grated cheese, onion, salt and pepper (no milk).

title: pickle squash
directions: Soak squash in 2/3 cup salt with just enough water to cover squash.
Boil syrup 15 minutes.
Then add squash and bring to a rolling boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pasta salad
directions: Pour dressing over broccoli, olives and tomatoes.
Cover. Marinate in refrigerator 3 hours; drain.
Add noodles, cheese and Bac*Os.
Toss lightly and serve.

title: jello pie
directions: Make jello according to package directions.
When it is half set, blend in the whipped cream and whip the cream and jello together.
Pour into the pie crust.
(Optional: Put Cool Whip on top or creme de menthe for decoration.)
Cool in refrigerator for approximately 3 to 4 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter.
Beat cream cheese, eggs, butter and sugar together.
Drain whole corn.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mamaw's oatmeal cake
directions: In boiling water, add oats.
Let stand 20 minutes, then add butter and sugars.
Mix with this the eggs, vanilla, flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain salmon; flake in small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 5 patties.
Brown on both sides.
Best served on toasted hamburger buns.

title: divinity candy
directions: In
saucepan over low heat, dissolve sugar, water, Karo and salt,
stirring.
Cook,
without
stirring, to 248°, firm ball stage,
then
remove
from heat and pour slowly over the stiffly beaten
egg whites.
Add vanilla and continue beating with	mixer until
mixture
will hold its shape and loses its gloss.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Put a pecan half on each spoonful.

title: hot asparagus rolls
directions: Cut off bread crust and slightly flatten with palm of hand or rolling pin.
Mix together cheeses and egg; spread on bread. Place 1 asparagus stalk on each bread slice; roll up and secure with toothpick.
Roll asparagus rolls in butter; put on cookie sheet and freeze.
When completely frozen, slice each roll into 3 pieces.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake about 15 minutes.
They will keep warm in oven forever.

title: sister lorene carroll's chocolate fudge icing
directions: In a mixing bowl, with a fork, stir sugar and cocoa well. Pour all other ingredients in medium size saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; boil for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: tunnel of fudge
directions: Soften butter.
Add eggs, 2 at a time.
Beat in between. Gradually add sugar.
By hand, stir in flour, 3 1/3 cups frosting and walnuts.
Pour in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool for 1 hour, then remove.
Cool to room temperature before adding glaze.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix water, oats and margarine and let stand 20 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and pour into a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
When you remove from oven pour on topping and broil a few minutes until topping is bubbly.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: low country boil
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a 3-gallon kettle and fill 1/3 of kettle with water.
Boil 30 minutes.
Can do earlier in day so seasonings can blend.
Fifteen minutes before serving, bring to a brisk boil.
Add sausage and cook for 5 minutes.
Add corn and cook 5 minutes.
Blend in shrimp and cook for last 4 minutes. Strain away pot liquid and serve immediately in large bowl.
Serve with cocktail sauce.
Let guests peel their own shrimp.
Place small bowls on table for hulls.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute butter, onions, celery and garlic.
Cook rice according to directions.
Add Rotel, cream of mushroom soup, Cheese Whiz, jalapenos and green pepper.
Add salt to taste.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: canned cherry pie
directions: Mix the ingredients in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Pour hot thickened juice over pitted cherries. Mix lightly. Pour into pastry-lined pie plate. Dot with 1 tablespoon butter. Cover with top crust which has slits cut in it. Bake until nicely browned and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust. Serve warm. Cover edges of pie with aluminum foil to keep edges from getting too brown.

title: chocolate chip banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a brownie tin.
Mix all of the ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour into the greased brownie tin.
Bake for 35 minutes or until brown.
Cut into squares.

title: busy mom's potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Cut into quarters.
Place potatoes, oil and dry soup in a 1/2-gallon Ziploc bag.
Vigorously shake the bag until the potatoes are thoroughly coated.
Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cinnamon cheesecake squares
directions: Spread one package of the crescent rolls in the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Beat the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread over crust.
Spread very carefully the second package of the crescent rolls over the top of the cream cheese mixture.
Be sure to cover completely.
Pour the melted butter over the top crust.

title: death of chocolate
directions: Prepare brownies and cool.
Prick with fork and pour Amaretto over brownies.
Prepare instant pudding.
Break brownies into pieces.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Mix the ingredients, except for the milk, in a suitable bowl. While beating, add milk, a little at a time, until you get a fluffy consistency.

title: chocolate marshmallow pops
directions: Melt chocolate, margarine and syrup in small saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Insert drinking straws (15) into marshmallows.
Dip each marshmallow into chocolate, turning until well coated.
Scrape off sides of marshmallow.
Roll in nuts, coconut, nonpareils or cereal.
Place on greased waxed paper.
Chill.
Makes 15 pops.

title: shrimp-crab casserole
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper with part of milk.
Beat out lumps. Add cheese to rest of milk in a double boiler.
When cheese has melted, add flour mixture and Tabasco sauce.
Stir until smooth and thickened.
Add shrimp and crab meat.
Pour in casserole; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 2 minutes.

title: white fruit dip
directions: With an electric mixer, fluff the cream cheese.
Add and mix marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Chill if desired and serve with fruit.

title: mulled wine blueberry sauce
directions: Pour the wine into a large skillet over high heat.
Add the peppercorns, allspice, vanilla, lemon zest, lemon juice, cinnamon sticks and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil; cook over high heat until the wine is reduced to 2 cups, about 15 minutes.
Strain and return to the pan.
Add the blueberries and sugar.
Bring to a boil again. Reduce the heat; cook just until the berries pop.
Use as a topping for pancakes, fruit shortcakes or spoon over ice cream. Makes 3 pints.

title: millionaire pie
directions: First, mix all of it together and then put it into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Let chill for 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans in bowl with hands.
Form a ball.
Roll in pecans.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: apricot chicken
directions: *Can also use 6 chicken breasts, 4 ounces apricot preserves, 3 ounces dressing and 1/2 package onion soup mix.

title: sweet potato chips(microwave)
directions: Cut sweet potatoes into thin slices. Sprinkle slices with cinnamon and sugar.
Microwave on High for 4 or 5 minutes.

title: main dish tater soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, butter and bay leaf over medium heat in a nonstick pan; stir almost constantly.
Add chicken broth.
Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Mix milk and flour in blender; add to potato mixture and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream and stir until smooth.
Garnish with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows, pour over and mix with remaining ingredients.

title: meat loaf hot dish
directions: Mix all together and put in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, then put mushrooms on top of meat loaf and make mashed potatoes and layer it on top of mushrooms and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake for 30 more minutes.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Place bacon in a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with paper towels. Microwave on High, 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp.
Remove bacon. Reserve drippings in pie plate.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Spread potatoes in pie plate.
Microwave uncovered at High, 6 to 7 minutes.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over potato mixture.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Microwave at High, 6 to 7 minutes, giving dish a quarter turn after 3 minutes. Sprinkle cheese and bacon.
Cover and microwave at High, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, then cut into wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening with sugar; beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flavoring.
Pour in tubed pan, which has been greased and floured.
Place in cold oven and then turn heat to 300° to 325° and bake for 60 minutes and then check to see when done.
Takes about a total of 80 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: "Nuke" each bag of vegetables for 5 minutes in microwave.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over vegetables.
Mix together.
Add 3/4 of the cheese and 3/4 of the onions.
Mix well. Add salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions on top and put back in oven for about 5 minutes, until top is crunchy and crispy.

title: very berry punch
directions: Pour juice into punch bowl; slowly pour carbonated beverage down side of bowl to prevent loss of carbonation.
Scoop sherbet and float on punch.
Makes 24 servings.

title: blue ribbon sugar cookies
directions: Mix eggs, shortening, butter and sugar.
Mix together dry ingredients and combine with first mixture.
Roll balls in sugar. Bake on greased cookie sheet after pressing ball down a little with bottom of sugared glass.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: yogurt shake (fat free)
directions: Blend in blender until mixed.
Add vanilla, chocolate or fruit.

title: quick fudge
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients in a double boiler over medium-high heat until melted.
Spread in cake pan, then refrigerate.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix and add 1 package Good Season Italian Dressing (prepared as directed) and 4 Tbsp. Salad Supreme Seasoning.

title: italian pita triangles(diabetic appetizers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brush pitas with margarine.
Sprinkle with garlic powder, basil and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into wedges; serve immediately. Yields 8 appetizers (1/4 pita round).

title: green pepper steak
directions: In a large saucepan, combine green pepper, onion, tomatoes, soy sauce, water and pieces of steak.
Bring to a rolling boil and turn down to low heat.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Can also be cooked in crock-pot.
Serve over rice.

title: grandpa's secret salted cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into bite size pieces.
Add Hawaiian salt and massage into cabbage until leaves turn darker green.
Add brown sugar and grated ginger and mix well.
If too salty, drain out liquid and mix in ice cubes.

title: impossible chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in pie plate.
Mix chicken, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, garlic powder, oregano, basil and tomato paste.
Spoon over Parmesan cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients in blender on high speed for 15 seconds, with hand beater for 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes longer or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until yellow disappears.

title: grandma's waffles
directions: Sift before measuring the flour.
Resift with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat well the egg yolks.
Add melted butter or oil and milk.
Combine liquid and dry ingredients with a few swift strokes.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Bake until golden.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
Make marinade of sugar, vinegar, salt and oil; pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate for 3 or 4 hours. Keeps 2 weeks refrigerated.
Tastes best if made 2 or 3 days before serving.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each.
Slowly add flour with baking powder mixed into flour. Alternate, adding flour and milk.
Beat in oil and vanilla.
Fold coconut into batter.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Let cool in pan.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Rinse fresh berries and drain well.
In saucepan, melt sugar and cornstarch.
Add water and lemon juice.
Stir until dissolved. Add berries and bring to a boil for 1 to 2 minutes or until clear and slightly thickened, stirring carefully to avoid crushing berries.
Serve warm or chilled over pancakes or white cake.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and about 1/2 of flour in the water.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Add egg, salt, Crisco and sugar.
Let rise about 40 minutes.
Stir down, roll out and cut.
Let rise to double in size.
Bake.

title: christmas fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits, pecans and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Stir remaining sugar and flavoring into whipped cream.
Chill thoroughly.

title: mocha walnut cookies
directions: Microwave 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Dissolve coffee in water. Cream together sugars, butter and dissolved coffee.
Add egg and melted chocolate chips.
Gradually add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips (and nuts, if desired).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet on both sides.
Place in flat baking dish.
Add Pepperidge Farm crumbs to drippings in skillet.
Stir to absorb drippings.
Spoon on top of each chop.
Pour milk around chops, not over dressing or it will float off.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Chops will absorb milk and dressing will brown.

title: chicken divan pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place cookie sheet in oven to preheat. In a medium saucepan, combine butter, flour and pepper.
Cook over low heat until mixture becomes thick and bubbly.
Gradually stir in broth and milk until mixture begins to thicken; add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir in chicken and broccoli.
Pour mixture into pie shell.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Place softened butter, sugar and egg in large mixing bowl. Beat until well creamed. Add chocolate; blend. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk/vanilla mixture to the butter and sugar mixture. Beat only long enough to form a soft dough, about 2 minutes. Add nuts and beat a few strokes. Drop from teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: banquette of chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Add chicken.
Cook until seared but not brown. In a small bowl, combine flour, nutmeg, salt, pepper and dill weed. Sprinkle over chicken and stir.
Cook over a low heat for 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add carrots, onion and chicken broth. Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Slowly stir in half and half to make a creamy sauce.
Serve over pasta or rice.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles using package directions.
Saute ground beef and sausage in skillet until brown.
Drain off drippings.
Add tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Place 1 layer of noodles on bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread layer of ground beef sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella over noodles. Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: corn meal muffins *
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Beat together the egg and milk and add to dry ingredients along with oil, stirring just enough to dampen.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: kahlua
directions: Dissolve coffee in water and cool. Add vanilla bean and vodka. Pour into container. Cover.
Let stand for 30 days.
Turn upside down once a week. Bottle. Makes great Sombreros, Black or White Russians.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix egg and milk together.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Shape into loaf and put into large loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain excess grease.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: montana tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Mix together the hamburger, taco seasoning and refried beans. Mix the sour cream and mushroom soup together.
Put half of the mushroom soup mixture, then hamburger mixture, then shells, then other half of mushroom soup mixture, then cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Eat with lettuce, tomatoes, salsa and French dressing.

title: sugarless applesauce cake(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine raisins, fruit and water in a saucepan; cook, uncovered, until water is evaporated and fruit is soft.
Set aside to cool.
In a large bowl, mix flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In another bowl, mix eggs, applesauce, sweetener, oil and vanilla.
Add nuts and reserved fruit mix.
Stir into dry mix.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan or 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: snicker salad
directions: Chop apples and snicker bars into very small pieces. Mix cool whip and cream cheese thoroughly, then add apples and snickers. Mix well. Refrigerate.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Season chicken with 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken and cook over medium-high heat for 5 to 7 minutes, until golden, turning once.
Remove with slotted spoon. Put onions and garlic in skillet and cook over medium heat 4 to 6 minutes, stirring occasionally, until onion is transparent.
Add tomatoes, water, paprika, caraway seed and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boil.
Return chicken to pan, 20 to 25 minutes over medium.
Stir occasionally.
Remove chicken.
Stir sour cream and flour into pan.
Whisk until smooth.
Boil until thickened.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Serve with noodles.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Combine lemon juice, soy sauce, sage, ginger, salt and pepper in casserole.
Let chicken stand in this mixture for several hours in the refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade (save).
Coat with flour and brown in hot fat.
Return chicken to marinade in casserole.
Add onions and juice.
Cover. Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: Soften yeast in water; add sugar, salt butter and eggs. Slowly add flour; beat well, scraping sides of bowl.
Mix until just stiff enough to knead.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Coat a bowl with butter and place dough in it.
Cover with a damp tea towel and allow to rise approximately 30 minutes.
Work dough down lightly, re-cover and allow to rise again for 30
minutes
Turn onto floured surface and roll into a 1 1/2-inch thick sheet.
To make filling,
brush butter on dough. Mix sugar, pecans and cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over dough and roll as a jelly roll; cut into thirds.
Braid thirds together and shape into a ring.
Cover with a warm damp cloth and let it treble in bulk.
Preheat oven to 425 degrees and bake for 30 minutes. Cool slightly.
Mix remaining ingredients to make a glaze and brush on top of bread and serve.

title: beef cabbage soup
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add 2 cups of water, bouillon cubes, cabbage, green pepper and garlic.
Bring to a boil; simmer 1/2 hour.
Add remaining vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are done, about 1/2 hour.

title: fudge sauce topping
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Blend in water.
Add milk. Bring to a boil.
Boil gently until thick, 3 to 4 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: spoon bread for two
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt margarine in small casserole.
Add boiling water to self-rising corn meal; mix well.
Add beaten egg, buttermilk and sugar; mix well.
Pour into heated casserole.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Brown meat and mushrooms in butter.
Add salt, sugar, tomato sauce and paste. In a separate bowl, mix cottage cheese, cream cheese, onions, pepper and sour cream.
Put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer with noodles and beef mixture.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease pie plate. Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (about 1 minute) in blender on high speed. Pour into pie plate. Bake about 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean. Let cool for 5 minutes before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bottle.
It is better to let it marinate for a couple of days or more.
I triple this recipe and keep in refrigerator for days.

title: blueberry buttermilk muffins
directions: In small bowl, combine buttermilk, melted butter and eggs until blended.

title: perfect pastry mix
directions: Mix flour and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly. Store in covered bowl in refrigerator for 1 month or less.
Toss with fork to lighten before measuring.
Mix 1/4 cup pastry mix with 2 or 3 tablespoons cold water for each 9-inch crust.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Wesson oil together and heat well. Holding cup high, add 1 pint of Wesson oil in thin stream, beating constantly.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick. Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° about 1 hour or toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: butter cookies for christmas
directions: Put powdered sugar in a little at a time.
Place well mixed dough in icebox and store overnight.
Roll thin on a floured board and cut out shapes.
Bake 5 minutes in 350° oven.
(May be cut in half).
Makes a lot.

title: peach cobbler supreme
directions: Melt butter in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add milk and stir well.
Pour into the baking dish. Do not stir.
Top with peaches, including juice.
Sprinkle nutmeg, cinnamon and lemon peel over peaches, but do not stir.
Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: winter squash dish
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cube the bread; brown in the butter.
Put on top of squash.
Place almonds on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Combine ingredients.
Let set overnight in refrigerator. Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on baking sheet. Cook in preheated oven at 350° until brown.
Yields approximately 75 to 100.

title: sesame flounder
directions: Place fillets in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Drizzle with lemon juice; sprinkle with pepper. Saute onion, green pepper and celery in apple juice concentrate until crisp-tender; spoon over fillets.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Put chops in pan.
Season to taste.
Slice onion on meat.
Mix orange juice and catsup well.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake 2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: lemon velvet cake
directions: Beat all ingredients well.
Bake in a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: easy congealed salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sour cream in mixing bowl.
Blend in dry jello.
Add pecans and drained fruit cocktail.
Put this mixture in a pan or dish.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours.

title: raspberry cream cheese bars
directions: In a mixing bowl cream the butter and brown sugar.
Combine the oats, flour, baking soda, and salt; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Press three-fourths of the mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 in. baking pan.
Bake at 350°F for 11-13 min. or until set and edges begin to brown.
Meanwhile in a small mixing bowl beat cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla; mix well.
Spread over crust.
Drop preserves by spoonfuls over cream cheese mixture. Spread evenly, mix nuts and oats. Sprinkle over preserves.

title: payday bars
directions: Combine syrup and sugar in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil. Stir constantly.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
In a large bowl, combine peanuts and cereal.
Pour hot mixture over cereal and nuts.
Stir carefully to coat the cereal.
Put mixture into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press down evenly with a rubber spatula.
When cool, cut into 24 squares.

title: pumpkin pie with butterscotch pudding
directions: Place pudding powder in saucepan.
Add spices and mix.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add pumpkin and mix thoroughly.
Turn into 9-inch pie shell.
Chill until firm.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dip meat in flour, brown.
Add onion, garlic and mushrooms; combine soup and seasonings; pour over meat.
Simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: p. t. a. punch
directions: Place frozen juice in punch bowl.
Add 1 cold Mt. Dew in punch bowl and keep adding as needed.
This punch has been served for all PTA and PTSO functions at Walker Elementary and Northside High School for the past 12 years.
I'm sure the tradition will continue with Northside Middle School.
The students
think you spend a lot of time on it and they love it;
you will love it too.

title: chocolate ice cream(tastes like a frosty)
directions: Let La Creme thaw enough so that you can mix it in with the other ingredients.
This will make 4 quarts.
Place in ice cream freezer and freeze as any other ice cream.

title: lime treat
directions: Mix gelatin as directed.
Drain pineapple and add to jello along with cottage cheese.
Chill until jello is set.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: harriet's cheese ball
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup nuts and 1/2 cup parsley.
Combine remaining ingredients until well mixed with beater or with hands.
Determine if you want 1 large or 3 to 4 smaller cheese balls.
Rip off approximate number of sheets aluminum foil and spread out on counter with piece of Saran Wrap on top of each.
Divide nuts and parsley equally on Saran.
Divide cheese mixture.
Shape into ball; roll in parsley/nut mixture.
Wrap in Saran, then foil, bringing up to top like Hershey's Kiss.
Freeze.
Thaw to serve.
Great with Wheat Thins or Ritz.

title: sticky buns
directions: Cut dough into 4 sections and then break into pieces as you dip into the following mixture.
Melt margarine; add sugar and cinnamon.
Place cherries and nuts into bottom of angel cake pan. Pour dough into pan.
Set oven at 200° and let dough rise for about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: ursula's candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut in strips twice the size of a French fry. Use a heavy saucepan.
Almost cover with water; put lid on loose. Cook 10 minutes.
Take cover off.
Add butter, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Cook 1 hour slow on medium heat.
Add Karo syrup.
Cook 1 more hour.
Occasionally give saucepan a good shake to keep from sticking.
Never stir!
The longer you cook, the better they are!

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix wet ingredients and add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350°. Makes 1 loaf and 1 layer cake.

title: love knots
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla in mixer until creamy, then add flour and baking powder, a little at a time to mixture to make dough.
Knead the dough about 5 to 10 minutes.
Roll into knots and bake for 12 minutes.
Rotate trays from bottom to top. Do not overbake.
They must be white, not brown.
Let cool.

title: maple-raisin crisps
directions: Mix oats and brown sugar in bowl.
Add oil, egg and maple flavoring; mix well.
Sift in flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Stir in raisins and pecans.

title: marshmallow fruit salad
directions: Drain can fruit well.
Add ingredients into bowl.
Mix with wooden spoon or spatula.
Mix well.
Set in refrigerator for 2-3 hours to set.
Serve cold.

title: chile con queso
directions: Combine Velveeta and milk in a medium saucepan over medium/low heat.
Stir often as cheese melts.
Be careful not to burn it.
When cheese is melted, add the remaining ingredients, but not the tomatoes.
Continue to cook over medium/low heat for 7 minutes, stirring often to prevent burning.
Stir in tomatoes and remove queso from heat.
Pour queso into a serving dish, top with crumbled ranchero cheese and serve with tortilla chips for dipping.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Combine all ingredients but tomato in blender; mix well.
Add tomato and chill.

title: make ahead oriental salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables well.
Combine in large bowl with pepper, onion and celery.
Stir gently.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill 24 hours before serving.
Drain before serving.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Stir well.
Toss with remaining ingredients.

title: icy punch
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Let cool slightly and add pineapple juice and orange juice.
Freeze in Tupperware container.
Let thaw about 4 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up until slushy.

title: egg and cheese souffle
directions: Cream together cheese and butter, spread on slice of bread and cut it in quarters.
Beat eggs well; add milk, salt and pepper. Put bread with cheese mixture on it in well-greased casserole. Pour egg and milk mixture over it and let stand overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: In a skillet break up the meat and fry until done, stirring constantly.
Drain off grease.
Stir onions into meat and saute a few minutes.
Put meat mixture in a casserole.
Add 2 cups of beans and 1 cup of brown sugar.
Spread catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin rice pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Stir in eggs.
Add evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Stir in rice and raisins. Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in pan with water to depth of 1 inch.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir mixture until well combined.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes more or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Place bread slices in a buttered 9 x 12-inch casserole. Cover with cheese and a layer of sausage.
Pour egg mixture over layers and sprinkle with a little extra cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: ham caribbean
directions: Trim fat from ham. Slash edges of ham at 1-inch intervals. Place on a rack in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crab mold
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise and Worcestershire sauce.
Add the rest. In a saucepan, put the cream soup and Knox gelatine and add 3 tablespoons water.
Mix together on low heat until gelatine dissolves.
Let cool.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers on a platter.

title: wedding champagne punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in punch bowl or large bowl.
Chill in freezer until slushy.
Add orange slices to punch 5 minutes before serving.

title: rouladen
directions: Serve over egg noodles, rice or salt potatoes.

title: all day roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast and brown, uncovered, at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes in a deep roasting pan.
Add onion soup mix, 3 cups boiling water and brown gravy to make gravy.
Add onion, carrots and potatoes, cut up, to pan.
Cover.
Turn oven to 225°; let cook for the day.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: If making peanut butter fudge, omit cocoa and add 1-1/2 cups peanut butter in place of pecans.

title: mexican independence day tamale pie
directions: In large skillet, brown meat with garlic powder, drain. In large
bowl,
mix
meat with remaining ingredients, except cornbread
mix
and
cheese.
Spoon
meat
mixture evenly into bottom of
a
x
9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Fold cheese into prepared
cornbread
mix.
Top meat mixture with cornbread and cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Put crackers, oil and spices in a double paper bag and shake well.
Store in a Tupperware container.

title: drunken stew
directions: Mix soup, onion mix and wine.
Pour over meat.
Cover and bake 3 hours in 300° oven.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onion, bell pepper, beef, salt, pepper and chili powder until done with lid on it.
Then add rice.
Place in pan to bake. Pour peas in center of mixture.
Dab butter, then pour tomatoes over top of all this and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: three thing pie
directions: Dissolve Hershey bar in double boiler.
Fold in Cool Whip, stirring well.
Put in pie shell and chill overnight.

title: strawberries and cream cake
directions: Generously spread one cake layer with frosting.
Top this with all of the sliced strawberries.
Spread the rest of the frosting on the second layer.
Do not frost the sides of the cake. Decorate the top of the cake with whole strawberries.
Refrigerate the cake until you are ready to serve it.

title: karen kuhlman's country club potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until knife soft.
Chop into bite size pieces.
Add mayonnaise, celery, relish, pickle juice, mustard, dill weed, salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with hard-boiled eggs.

title: chili enchiladas
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cans chili, 2 tablespoons onion and 1 cup cheese; set aside.
Spoon 1/3 cup of chili mixture in center of each taco shell.
Roll up; place seam side down in ungreased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Spoon remaining chili over all. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and onion on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine water, oats and butter.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Beat sugar and eggs together.
Add to oat mixture.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool cake 15 to 20 minutes.
Put topping on cake and put under broiler for 1 to 2 minutes until it bubbles.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute seafood in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add sherry gradually. Add white sauce; stir to blend.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix the cans with the ginger ale and add either the champagne or sherbet just before serving.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Mel butter in saucepan.
Add flour and stir.
Add milk, salt, pepper and mustard.
Stir until thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Meanwhile, cook potatoes until almost tender.
Drain. Pour potatoes in casserole bowl.
Pour cheese mixture over potatoes.
Add ham mix.
Dot with ham cubes.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: marshy muffins
directions: Mix together as normal muffins, except mash 1/2 cup blueberries and add to ingredients.
Add the rest of blueberries by hand and mix in.
Sprinkle muffins with granulated sugar before baking.
Pour into greased muffin cups and bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sweet potatoes casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.

title: karen's chili
directions: Cook beef and sausage. Add all ingredients to crock-pot and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Layer in order listed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° covered for 35 to 45 minutes, until bubbly.

title: carrot chicken with rice
directions: Add crushed garlic, butter, lemon juice, salt, pepper and honey to chicken; cook until lightly brown.
Add mushrooms and carrot; cook 5 minutes on medium heat.
Serve over rice with broccoli pieces.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; beating well.
Pour into a lightly greased and floured 10-inch pie plate. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add slightly beaten egg and fruit cocktail.
Put into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Put in jar or coffee can and stir until well blended.
To make 1 cup or mug, put 2 teaspoons in cup; add hot water.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown ground meat in large skillet.
Drain fat.
Mix in Ro-Tel and cream.
Cook on low heat.
Cream will scorch easy.
Cut cheese into cubes and mix into meat mixture.
Let simmer for 20 minutes or so.
Cajun seasoning can be added for spicier taste.
Pour over Fritos and eat.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes on low.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Mix bread crumbs with hamburger; shape into balls and brown. Mix tomatoes, soup, water, spices, seasonings, onion, green pepper and celery.
Add meat balls; simmer for several hours.
Serve spaghetti with meat balls and sauce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hunter's stew
directions: Let each person in camp fix their own dinner.
Wrap in 2 layers of foil.
Put veggies on foil first.
Season and put meat on top.
Wrap foil.
Cook over coals for 1 hour.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and egg.
Drop and press down with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: ohio state devil's food cake
directions: Combine cocoa, boiling water and soda; let cool while creaming shortening.
Add sugar gradually, creaming thoroughly.
Add cocoa mixture after each egg.
Add unbeaten eggs.
Add milk and flour alternately, beginning with flour and ending with flour.
This makes a large cake.
Can be made in three layers.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: almond brittle bars
directions: Cream butter or margarine until light and fluffy.
Beat in the vanilla.
Add the sugar slowly and continue creaming until well blended.
Beat in the egg yolk.
Stir in the flour and combine thoroughly.
(Do not beat in or the cookies will be tougher.)
Pat mixture into a lightly greased 15 x 10-inch baking pan.

title: spanish rice(arroz con tomate)
directions: In skillet, cook green pepper, onion, garlic, basil and rosemary in hot oil until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rice, chopped tomatoes, salt, pepper and 2 cups water.
Cook, covered, over low heat for about 20 minutes, or until rice is done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: granny's barbecue
directions: Cook meat until tender; flake and finely chop meat.
Blend all ingredients in large bowl except catsup and barbecue sauce.
If mixture is a little sour add more sugar.
Add catsup and barbecue sauce as needed.
Boil until thick, stirring often.
Pour over meat and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over buns with cole slaw if desired.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread and butter lightly on one side.
Crumble sausage and cook until lightly browned.
Drain.
Lay out 6 slices of bread in a 3-quart casserole, buttered side up.
Sprinkle half of the sausage and half of the cheese over bread.
Repeat with bread, sausage and cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk and salt. Pour over sausage and cheese.
Press down on bread until milk comes through.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until puffed and brown.
Serves 6.

title: dirty rice
directions: Chop seasonings. Fry sausage. Add livers and fry until done. Add seasonings to meat and cook for about 10 minutes. Add 1 cup of water and let boil. Add cooked rice. Add Accent, garlic salt and pepper to taste. Prepare Uncle Ben's rice according to directions on box. Add to other ingredients.

title: beef brisket
directions: Marinate with Season-All salt, lemon juice and any other seasonings you want.
Cook in low oven (150°), covered, overnight or until done.
Serve with barbecue sauce.

title: decorator icing
directions: Beat Crisco, salt and water until thoroughly mixed. Then add cornstarch, flavoring and powdered sugar one cup at a time. Beat for 5 minutes or until icing is very creamy. Great for decorating cakes. Keeps well in a sealed bowl in the refrigerator.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Pour
milk
over cracker crumbs and mix all ingredients together.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: filled sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Beat eggs and vanilla until fluffy and add to shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in sour milk (which can be made by adding vinegar or lemon juice to whole milk) and flour mixture.
Stir well.
Chill dough in refrigerator for several hours.
Turn out dough on lightly floured surface; roll and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place a teaspoon of filling on each bottom piece.
Seal with another.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal clusters
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a full boil for one minute, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and peanut butter; stir until smooth.
Add oats and mix well.
Cool slightly until mixture holds shape.
Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper or use 1 teaspoon for dipping up, then push off with a second teaspoon.
Allow to cool, then store in a tightly covered container.

title: hoosier pudding
directions: Slice cake crossways into 3 layers; separate.
Prepare pudding using 2 1/2 cups milk.
Stir in 2 cups Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 pudding mixture on bottom layer; top with 1/3 pineapple and cherries (split in half).
Repeat with second layer.
Place third layer on top.
Frost entire cake with Cool Whip.
Garnish with pineapple and cherries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chris' mayonnaise
directions: Whizz egg yolks in blender with a dash of vinegar, then pour in oil in a thin stream until mixture emulsifies.
Add more oil and a small amount of vinegar until desired texture, then add mustard, garlic, salt, pepper and tarragon.

title: pepparkakor
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves onto waxed paper.
In a large bowl of electric mixer, with the mixer at high speed, beat the butter, granulated sugar and 1 egg until light and fluffy.
Add molasses and lemon peel. Beat until well blended. With wooden spoon, stir in flour mixture; mix with hands until well blended and smooth. Divide the dough into 4 parts.
Wrap each part separately and refrigerate overnight.

title: rice shrimp casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with cheese and paprika. Bake in moderate oven until bubbly and cheese has melted.
Based on 6 servings: 268 calories per serving; 10 g. fat; 555 mg. sodium; 91 mg. cholesterol.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat butter; brown mushrooms slightly.
Heat cream in a separate pan.
Take off heat; stir in egg yolks vigorously, a little at a time.
Still stirring, add Mozzarella and 1 cup Parmesan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add cream and cheese mixture to ziti and mushrooms.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan on casserole. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: lazy pot roast
directions: Place beef in a roaster or casserole.
Sprinkle a package of dry onion soup mix over meat.
Add soup mixture.
Cover and bake at 325° until tender (about 45 minutes per pound).
Serve with the gravy that has formed.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Add nuts and mix well.
Spread quickly in buttered 9 x 5-inch pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saut onions and peppers in butter. Combine all ingredients. Pour in casserole dish and bake at 400° to 425° until brown on top.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt and shortening with pastry blender until it resembles coarse meal.
Then add water, stirring with fork.
Bake at 425° until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: speedy sweet potato pie
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes or until a knife inserted into the center of the pie comes out clean.
Cool.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add mashed bananas to creamed mixture.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add the beaten eggs and flour mixture to the first mixture; mix well.
Fold in the 6 ounces of sour cream and nuts.
Bake in two greased 8 1/2 x 5-inch loaf pans for one hour at 300°.

title: country brunch skillet
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp. Remove bacon; crumble and set aside. Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons bacon drippings. Add potatoes, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper to drippings; cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are browned and tender (approximately 12 to 15 minutes).

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add marshmallow cream; mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip topping; mix until smooth.
Pour into 8-inch baking dish and place fruit selected on top.
Or serve plain.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.
Make own graham cracker crust for 8-inch baking dish.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon and egg with fork.
Add 1/2 cup sifted flour and stir (mixture will be thick).
Add pepper, onions and Worcestershire sauce.
In the 1/4 cup salmon juice, put the baking powder; beat with fork until it foams.
Pour this into salmon mixture and mix with fork.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with 1 teaspoon salt; let stand for 30 minutes.
Combine next 6 ingredients in large salad bowl.
Next add mushrooms and scallions.
Drain and pat dry cucumbers; add to the bowl, then add parsley, tomatoes and green pepper.
Cover; chill 4 hours.
Just before serving, add Swiss cheese and toss then.
Add garnish of hard-boiled egg slices.

title: * catch-all casserole *
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water for 15 minutes; drain.
Mix in corn, string beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce and cheese.
Cut in small pieces.
Brown hamburger and add to mixture.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and freeze.

title: hashed brown-cheese casserole
directions: Place potatoes in colander.
Let stand until completely thawed and excess moisture has drained off.
Combine sour cream, soup and butter.
Mix well.
Add salt, onion and cheese; mix well.
Blend in potatoes.
Place mixture in shallow 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven (350°) about 50 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
Do not assemble over 2 hours before baking.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In medium bowl mix the crushed pretzels, melted butter and 3 tbsp. sugar. Press firmly into 10 inch dish pie pan or casserole dish. Bake 8 minutes. Set aside to cool.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix together until well blended.
Spread on 8 slices of ham. Roll and fasten with toothpicks.
Chill for 12 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, rice, sugar, and salt in large pot.
Cook over high heat stirring occasionally until boiling.
Reduce to medium heat for 45 to 60 minutes;
stirring every few minutes so mixture does not stick to bottom of pan.

title: carrots
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, allspice, pepper and lemon juice in pan over low heat until blended.
Drain carrots and add to pan. Simmer about 3 minutes until flavors are blended.
Serve immediately.

title: sesame seed refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix ingredients; roll 1 1/2 inch in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate.
Slice 1/4 inch in thickness.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: homemade beans
directions: Cook beans until done.
Cook onion, pepper and bacon.
Combine ingredients with beans and simmer for 2 hours.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Melt butter and chocolate. Remove from heat; stir in sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; beat lightly just until blended. Don't overbeat. Stir in flour and nuts. Spread batter in pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes. Cool. Cut.

title: chocolate-pecan fudge
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat; stir in cocoa.
Stir in confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Add evaporated milk.
Stir constantly over low heat until warm and smooth.
Add pecan pieces.
Pour into foil lined 8-inch square pan; chill. Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 5 dozen squares.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Cook beans and drain.
Chop onion. In casserole dish, add soup, beans, onion, bacon and cheese.
Top with french-fried onions.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ita's fajitas
directions: Cut fajitas in thin strips; season with meat tenderizer and garlic salt to taste.
Set aside in refrigerator.
Slice next four ingredients into thin strips.
Brown fajitas in oil.
Add sliced vegetables and cook until tender.
Pour over hot iron skillet and squeeze orange over fajitas.
Serve sizzling hot.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Remove cartilage from crab meat.
In a large bowl, blend the cream cheese, sour cream, salad dressing, lemon juice, Worcestershire, dry mustard, garlic and milk.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Fold crab into mix with 2+ tablespoons of Cheddar cheese.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking bowl.
Top with remaining Cheddar.
Bake at 325° until brown and bubbly (approximately 30 minutes).
Best served with stone wheat crackers.

title: pat's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix and bring to a boil in a heavy pan the sugar, oleo and milk.
Stir constantly until soft ball stage (10 to 12 minutes). Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme. Stir well.
Add nuts, if you like.
Pour into a 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: sandy's fabulous "corn stuff"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On stove top, melt butter in casserole. Mix in creamed and plain corn, sour cream and Jiffy mix.
Bake in 2-quart covered casserole (8 x 8-inch) for 1 1/2 hours covered and 30 minutes, uncovered.
Makes 6 servings.

title: texas french dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar.
Shake vigorously.
Makes 1 quart.

title: broiled fish fillets
directions: Arrange fillets in broiler pan.
Brush with lime juice.
Broil for 6 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients in small bowl.
Mix well. Spread over fillets.
Broil for 2 minutes longer.
Makes 3 servings.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Set oven to 400°.
Heat 1-inch salted water to a boil.
Add broccoli. Cover and cook until almost tender (about 5 minutes). Drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, cheese, onion and green pepper in greased 10-inch pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
