Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out water.
You may also use a microwave to defrost but do not cook.
Add sour cream, Ranch dressing, chopped water chestnuts and spinach.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Serve in hollowed out pumpernickel round loaf.
Cut hollowed bread pieces to dip.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt butter; add green pepper and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove pepper and mushrooms.
Blend in flour, milk, broth and seasonings and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce boils.
Add chicken, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook until chicken is heated.
Serve hot over biscuits.

title: mamaw atwood's pound cake(club member: laine shoemake)
directions: Put in long greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until cooked, drain and rinse in cold water. Put macaroni in boil.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: cherry nut salad
directions: Pour Eagle Brand condensed milk into large bowl; add cherry pie filling, pineapple (drained), Cool Whip and pecans.
Mix well with spoon and refrigerate overnight.

title: meat balls and baked beans
directions: Combine milk, ground beef, cracker meal, egg, chopped onions, garlic salt, salt and mustard; mix thoroughly. Shape into balls. Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: one dish fruit salad
directions: A little coconut and other fruit may be added.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in covered jar or container until ready to use.
(Makes a great going-away gift for college, etc.) For 1 serving, place 1 to 2 teaspoons mix in micro-proof cup.
Add water or cider; cook on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Makes 64 servings.

title: broccoli-ham ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop ham, broccoli, onion and parsley.
Coarsely grate cheese; mix all ingredients except rolls and set aside.

On flat stone or cookie sheet, arrange crescent rolls in a circle with bases overlapping and point to the outside. There should be a circle about 3-inches in diameter in center. Spoon filling over bases at the center.
Fold points of triangle over filling and tuck under bases at the center.
Filling will not be completely covered.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grits casserole
directions: Add 1 cup chopped onion to sausage after all grease is removed and cook, stirring often for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cut and steam broccoli.
Melt cheese, and mix with broccoli. Add heavy whipping cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Water or milk can be added to reach desired consistency.

title: hot salad dressing(can be used for lettuce or endive.)
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
Blend the flour into the grease and brown.
Add the vinegar and stir until thickened.
Mix together the sugar and pepper; add to the mixture.
Pour over the beaten egg yolk; mix well.
Put on heat again and cook 1 minute longer.
Add the bacon bits and stir.
Pour over salad while still hot.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and water and vinegar.
Boil until syrup hairs.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Form into balls.
Eight ounces of chocolate syrup can be added to sugar, water and syrup mixture in beginning.

title: barb's potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes; dice celery, onion and carrots.
Cook carrots, celery and onions for 5 minutes.
Then add potatoes and cook 10 minutes longer or until potatoes are done.
Add oleo, salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: purple cow shake
directions: Pour juice and milk in blender.
Add ice cream.
Blend 30 seconds.
Serve.

title: fideo mexicano (vermicelli)
directions: In a large skillet, add enough cooking oil to cover bottom. Add the vermicelli (crushing the noodles a little) into the heated cooking oil.
Stir on medium high to brown the vermicelli.	Add onions and continue to stir until onions are translucent.
Add the remaining ingredients, mixing well. Put on lowest heat, cover and cook until vermicelli is soft (about 15 to 20 minutes). During this period, DO NOT STIR, as it will make the pasta mushy.

title: macaroni sauce
directions: Put tomatoes in large saucepan.
Let it come to a boil, crush it and let it
boil for about 40 minutes uncovered.
Add drippings from Meatballs and	Sausage
and the meat.	Let boil for another 1/2 hour with
the meat.
At same time you add the meat add the basil, about 3
to 4 leaves or 1 teaspoon dry and salt.
Then put in the
tomato
paste with the water and sugar and	let boil another
minutes.
Stir
often	thoroughly. Serve with your favorite pasta.
Skim sauce if necessary.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Make a sauce with butter, flour and milk.
When thickened and smooth, remove from fire.
Add chopped onion and cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Add beaten egg yolks and blend well. Carefully add the asparagus, cut in small pieces.
Season to taste. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish and bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 30 minutes or until center is slightly firm.
Serves 6.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Blend all the ingredients together in a glass baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, covered.
Serve hot with tortilla chips, salsa and sour cream.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container or blender.
Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 1 cup, about the same amount as a can of commercial type, but at a lower cost.
Use in pies, candies, frostings and desserts.

title: spice marinade for meat
directions: Mix ingredients together and set aside in a covered jar for whenever you need it.

When you're ready to marinate the meat, for every 3 to 4 pounds of meat, put 2 tablespoons of the dry mixture, 1 medium onion, 2 garlic cloves, 2 tablespoons olive oil and 2 tablespoons lemon juice in a food processor and blend.
Smear over the meat and let marinate in the refrigerator overnight or at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours before grilling.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients; put into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix the flour and potatoes together.
Add the eggs and salt. Fry the pancakes to a crispy brown.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into four pieces, trim fat.
Coat steak with flour. In dutch oven, pour oil and brown meat over medium-high setting. Add tomatoes, soup, celery salt and onion rings.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook over a low heat for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry milk shake
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Cover and blend (liquefy) until smooth.
Makes about 2 (8-ounce) servings.

title: lemon-sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Combine sour cream and milk. Stir until smooth.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in lemon and vanilla extracts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: thicken strawberries
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together with cold water. Add everything else together, except berries; cook until thick. Pour over berries.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat margarine and shortening with electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 of the flour, egg, sugar, milk, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill for 3 hours.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with 1 can of pecan and coconut frosting or German chocolate frosting.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: In a large bowl mix all the ingredients and set aside.
Then use my Never Fail Pie Crust recipe and make 2 pie crusts.
(The recipe makes 3 crusts, you can save the remaining dough in a Ziploc bag.
It will keep for days in refrigerator, or you can go ahead and roll out crust in an aluminum pie pan and put in plastic bag and freeze for later use).
Use a deep pie pan.
Spray with nonstick spray.
Lay first crust, then pour in turkey mixture. Then fold top crust and make 3 cuts 1 1/2 inches long at a slant. Move 1/2-inch on each side and repeat.
Then open crust and lay over the top.
Gently go around the pie and tuck the top crust behind the bottom crust.
Use fork and press together or finger fan around crust.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine;
gradually
add
sugar,
beating until light and fluffy.
Add
egg
and beat until mixture is smooth. Combine flour and soda;
add
to peanut butter mixture, mixing until
well blended.
Shape
dough into 1 inch balls and then place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten into 2 inch
rounds with
a
fork in a cross hatch pattern.
Bake at 350°
for	8
to 10	minutes or until firm.	Transfer to wire racks to cool. Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: mini meat loaves wrapped in bacon
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Shape mixture into 6 loaves.
Crisscross 2 half slices bacon on each loaf.
Tuck ends under loaf.
Place on shallow baking pan.
Bake uncovered for 50 minutes.

title: green pea-bacon salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: mel's macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients in large mixing bowl in order given.
Add mayonnaise until desired consistency.
Add milk.
Mix well. Chill. Enjoy!

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add flour alternating with lemonade. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes. After baked, brush with lemonade.

title: never fail divinity fudge
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water together and boil until mixture will spin a thread when dropped from a spoon.
Have egg whites beaten stiff and pour half of syrup into egg white a little at a time, beating hard.
Return other half of the syrup to heat and cook until it will form a ball when dropped in a cup of cold water.
Mix all together, beating well and add nuts, salt and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into lightly greased pan or dish.
When cold, cut into squares.

title: roast beef and gravy
directions: Cover the bottom of baking pan with foil.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Season roast with salt, pepper and garlic.
Place in pan with dry soup mix around.
Add soup and cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes per pound or until done.
If more gravy is desired, double sugar, dry soup mix and cream of chicken soup. Gravy is delicious!

title: momma's eggplant fritters
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Cook in water over medium heat about 30 minutes; drain, rinse and mash eggplant.
Add eggs and salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter; add to eggplant mixture.
Add enough cornmeal to form patties. Heat 1/4 inch of oil in skillet to frying temperature.
Drop from spoon into heated skillet.
Cook approximately 15 minutes until browned on both sides.

title: angel food trifle
directions: Alternate 3 layers each of cake pieces, pudding and whipped topping in a 3-quart serving bowl.
Garnish the top with the almonds and cherries for a festive holiday dessert.
Best to refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: turkey chilli(low-fat)
directions: Brown ground turkey, onion, salt and pepper.
Add chilli seasoning, chilli beans and salsa.
Add tomato juice if you want thinner chilli.
Simmer about 1 hour and serve.

title: cheese cake
directions: Spread 1/2 crumb mixture in bottom of large pan (9 x 13-inch). Pour in jello.
Cover with rest of crumbs.
Place in refrigerator and chill.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chopped chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain veg-all and sprinkle over chicken.
Chop eggs over veg-all.
On top of stove, melt butter in large pan and blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in broth and milk.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over chicken mixture. Top with biscuits.
Bake in preheated 400° oven till biscuits are done.

title: donna's hot dish
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender, then drain.
Put macaroni and rest of the ingredients into baking dish, mixing well.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.

title: green beans caesar
directions: Cook beans. Cut into 1-inch pieces. Heat oven to 350°. Toss beans with salad oil, vinegar, onion, salt, garlic and pepper. Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole. Stir together bread crumbs, cheese and butter. Sprinkle over beans. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake uncovered 15 to 20 minutes or until heated.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; spoon off fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package; drain.
Combine rest of ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.
Set aside.
Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; spread with half the cottage cheese mixture. Add 1 package Mozzarella cheese and then half the meat sauce. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
If so, allow 15 minutes longer in oven when baking.
Layer:
noodles, cheese mixture, Mozzarella cheese and meat mixture.
Repeat.

title: cream cheese chewies
directions: Mix together.
Pour over cake and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Mix all dry ingredients together.

Cut shortening into dry mixture until it resembles fine crumbs. Add milk; stir gently until the dough holds together. Turn onto lightly floured board and knead about 12 strokes. Do not overwork the dough. Just roll it into balls using your hands or use a rolling pin. Arrange biscuits about 1 inch apart on a baking sheet; bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lebkuchen
directions: Mix together the honey with 1/4 pound sugar.
Boil, skim and cool.
Then add sifted cake flour.
In separate pan, mix the brown sugar and 1/4 pound white sugar, eggs, spices and soda which has been dissolved in brandy, citron, orange peel, lemon peel, grated lemon rind and baking powder.
Mix the nuts with the all-purpose flour and add to the batter.

title: indian candy was-nah
directions: Mix well, refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll into small balls and serve or store in refrigerator.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle onion over potatoes.
Melt butter, pour half over potatoes and onion. Put cheese, soup and sour cream in boiler and heat until well mixed.
Pour over potato mixture and stir well.
Add rest of butter to bread crumbs.
Spread on top of mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients together and add to cabbage several hours prior to serving.
Makes enough for a family of 8.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter or margarine in an 8 x 11 x 2-inch size pan.
Set aside.

title: swiss steak
directions: In large skillet, brown steak.
Add tomato sauce, pepper strips, onion and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with seasonings; simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice or creamed potatoes.

title: claire's peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread lots of peanut butter on one side of each piece of bread.

This will keep the jelly from soaking through the bread. Put lots of jelly on top of the peanut butter on one slice of bread, and place the other slice of bread, peanut butter side down, on top of the jelly.
Flip the sandwich over so that the slice of bread with jelly on it is now on top.
This allows gravity to pull the jelly down to the peanut butter on the other slice.
Help gravity out by "smooshing" the slices of bread together so that the jelly sort of sticks to the peanut butter.
Don't cut the sandwich. It's ready to eat.
Just take a bite and offer some to a passerby.

title: green chili canapes
directions: Mix and spread on bread.
Broil until puffy and brown.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/2 cake in bottom of punch bowl or large glass pan, then pour 1 pudding mix, prepared, over cake, then 1/2 pineapple, then 1/2 can pie filling, 1/2 coconut and 1/2 pecans.
Repeat with remaining ingredients in layers.
Chill overnight.
Drain maraschino cherries, chop and place on top for looks.

title: pepperoni bites
directions: For filling:
In a bowl, combine Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni and pizza sauce.
Set aside.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in gallon container that is airtight.
To make 1 cup hot cocoa, use 3 tablespoons of mix per 1 cup boiling water; stir.
Top with marshmallows.

title: cheerio nuggets
directions: Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt in a saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly around edges. Continue stirring 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda until mixture is foamy.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt margarine and blend in brown sugar.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring.
Add milk and continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Blend in powdered sugar gradually.
Add vanilla and mix well.

title: grounded skroodles
directions: In large Dutch oven, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from pot and set aside.
Saute onions in bacon grease.
Add ground round; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and fry until browned.
Stir and mash while it is frying until it becomes crumbly.
Return bacon to pot and add the next 10 ingredients (green peppers, tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning, Worcestershire sauce, Parmesan cheese and sugar).
Mix together and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cook noodles according to box.
Drain and add to sauce.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: honolulu seafood salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Immediately drain in a colander. Rinse with cold water and drain.

title: unbelievable lasagne
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread about 1 cup sauce; arrange a layer of uncooked lasagne.
Top with some sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan and sauce.
Repeat.
End with a final layer of lasagne; pour remaining sauce.
Make sure all lasagne is covered.
Top with Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Allow to stand for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients in dutch oven or other large pot.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
No need to brown meat.
Serve over noodles or rice.	Makes large quantity.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread the rolls in a lightly greased 12 pizza pan, pressing the perforations to seal them. Combine the eggs, bacon, cheese and mushrooms, pour over the crust. Bake at 375°f. 190°c. gas mark 5 for 12-15 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: *Reserve 1/4 cup crumbs to sprinkle on top.

title: w. w. chocolate cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add all other ingredients.
Beat on low speed until well beaten or blended.
Divide evenly into 2 cake pans.
Spray pans well with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add jam, then eggs, milk and flour. Mix by hand and add other ingredients. Mix and bake in 4 greased and floured pans and bake at 375° until done. Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then cool on racks.

title: mint patties
directions: In mixer bowl, add Karo, margarine and extract.
Beat.
Stir in sugar, one cup at a time.
Turn out onto sugared surface. Knead, adding sugar until stiff.
Divide into 2 sections.
Add food coloring.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Flatten with a fork.
Let them sit on waxed paper overnight.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts; press out in baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: sidewalk paint
directions: Mix cornstarch and water.
Add food coloring and stir. Repeat to make more colors.
Washes away with water.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all together with mayonnaise and dill pickle juice to taste.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind tomatoes, onions and peppers in food processor and chop; pour off juice.
Add to vinegar, brown sugar and salt.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking.
Mix the cornstarch and mustard with enough water to make a paste.
Add to mixture and cook 2 minutes.
Then add mayonnaise.
Stir well.
Fill hot sterilized jars to top and seal airtight.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: german bacon slaw
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Dice or crumble bacon and reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Combine drippings with vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Toss cabbage with onion, green pepper and celery.
Add dressing just before serving.
Garnish with bacon bits.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients, except 1 cup cracker crumbs, saved to	sprinkle
on top of casserole.	Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in boiling water until tender but not mushy.
Drain and cool. Combine next four ingredients in medium saucepan.
Stir in apricot nectar, hot water, and orange peel. Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter.
Cool slightly; stir in pecans.
Cut sweet potatoes in halves and place in casserole.
Pour sauce over potatoes so all are glazed.
If desired, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, in 375° oven for 25 minutes, or until sauce is bubbling. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blend together 1 cup mayonnaise, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons vinegar.
Mix vegetables and raisins together and chill.
Just before serving, add 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 pound bacon (cooked crisp and crumbled).

title: finnish pancakes
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk and eggs lightly with beater, then add sugar, salt and flour.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 23 minutes.
Serve with maple syrup, jelly or butter.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Add butter.
Pare potatoes; slice and arrange in buttered baking dish.
Pour over 1/3 syrup and bake until brown in moderate oven (350°), basting twice with remaining syrup.
Serves 6.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix mustard, salt, pepper and flour.
Dredge steak in mixture. Brown well in fat.
Put into roasting dish and sprinkle meat with onions, carrots, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and tomatoes. Cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fred's no-cook strawberry jam
directions: Clean strawberries and crush thoroughly, one layer at a time, measuring 4 cups into a large bowl.
Combine pectin with 1/4 cup sugar.
Gradually add pectin mixture to fruit, stirring vigorously.
Set aside for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: florida hush puppies
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, salt, baking powder and pepper in bowl. Add milk and eggs.
Stir to blend.
Add onion and blend.
More milk or cornmeal may be needed after onion is added to produce desired consistency.
(Hush Puppies should be fried after fish is fried as heat should be reduced somewhat for them.)

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook meat, onions and peppers together; drain.
Mix flour and tomatoes.
Add meat to vegetable mixture, then spices and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
In 2-quart baking dish, sprayed with nonstick spray, layer noodles, cheese and meat mixture.
Sprinkle evenly with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Stir together crumbs, sugar, cocoa and butter.
Press onto bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a larger mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then peanut butter chips until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Pour over crust.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Refrigerate.

title: nutty ham and cheese
directions: Combine cream cheese, pecans, onion and garlic salt.
Spread on roll.
Layer remaining ingredients.
May be heated in foil.

title: cherry salad
directions: Cook cherries, pineapple and sugar to boiling point.
Add jello to hot mixture, stirring well to dissolve jello.
A few drops of red food coloring may be added, if desired.
When partially congealed, add nuts and refrigerate.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on.
Cool, peel and grate.
Melt butter and mix with soup; mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Mix well.
Add potatoes and mix again.
Bake in a 3-quart casserole 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: a good teacher
directions: Mix this together in a crock-pot.
Boil on low for 5 months. Then add a spot of glue and a sprinkle of baking soda.
Drop on the floor and you've got a good teacher.

title: herbed lentils and rice
directions: Combine broth, lentils, onion, uncooked rice, wine and seasonings.
Stir 1/2 of cheese into lentil mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart ungreased casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until lentils and rice are tender, stirring twice. Top casserole with remaining cheese; return to oven.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Dissolve jello in hot water; add syrup and chill slightly.
Add cranberry mixture, pineapple, nuts and celery.
Pour into mold, chill until firm.
Serve on crisp lettuce.
Pass mayonnaise.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry ground beef with onion and drain off fat.
Combine spaghetti sauce to beef.
Cook lasagna until done; drain off water.
In a large cake pan, put a layer of lasagna, then a layer of beef and sauce, then one each of the cheeses until everything is used, usually about 3 layers.
Then put into the oven about 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: mexican cheese bake
directions: Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick together until smooth.
Before pouring into dishes, sprinkle 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese into each dish.
Pour Bisquick mixture over cheese, dividing equally between the two dishes.
Bake 25 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: banana cake
directions: Mash bananas fine; add lemon juice.
Mix in buttermilk.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, then vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hacienda dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, salsa and salt until well blended.
Spread cheese mixture in microwaveable pie plate or bowl.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together and bake 25 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Do not grease.)
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard.
Add bread cubes, cheese, mushrooms and sausage.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Drain pineapple and mix into jello.
Mix cranberry sauce into jello.
Let set slightly and add nuts.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Strain the juice from the cans of fruit and mix the dry instant pudding in and stir.
Pour over fruit and refrigerate.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Pour into greased 11 1/2 x 8 1/2 baking pan. Bake in preheated 400° oven 25 to 30 minutes, until edges are golden brown.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Mix vegetables together.
Mix oil, sugar, salt and vinegar together and pour over vegetables.
Best prepared 24 hours before serving.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook peas, drain and cool.
Cut up hard-boiled eggs.
Combine all ingredients and add enough mayonnaise to hold together. Refrigerate and serve.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Fry hamburg with chopped onion. Drain excess grease. Add tomatoes and enough water to make 2 quarts. Add barley, salt, parsley and pepper. Simmer for 1 hour. Add mixed vegetables and simmer for another 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat condensed milk and cream cheese to a smooth consistency. Pour in large bowl containing drained fruit cocktail, pineapple tidbits, mandarin oranges and diced apple.
Blend thoroughly. Chill or freeze an hour before serving.
Yields 15 servings.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Heat margarine in a heavy saucepan or skillet.
Add and saute onion and pepper.
Add flour; stir and cook until bubbly.
Add chicken broth, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Add chicken and parsley. Heat through and serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate. Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until coated.
Press into a greased 9-inch pie pan.

title: quick pepper jelly
directions: Combine jelly and pepper in small saucepan.
Cook, stirring over low heat until jelly melts, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to small bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Mix cabbage with onion and pepper.

title: slumgullion
directions: Heat shortening in skillet.
Brown beef; drain.
Combine all ingredients, except pickle, in slow cooker; stir.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.
Stir in chopped pickle.
Makes 8 servings.

title: snicker pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, place in pie pan and freeze.

title: peanut butter and chocolate pizza
directions: Beat margarine and peanut butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds in a medium-size bowl.
Add 1/2 cup of the flour, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat or stir in remaining flour. Press dough evenly onto a 12 or 14-inch pizza pan that has been lightly greased, forming a rim around the edge.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes more, or until marshmallows are puffy and lightly browned.
Immediately sprinkle with M&M's.
Cool, cut into wedges. Makes about 10 slices.
Kids love it!

title: artichoke heart dip
directions: Mince artichoke hearts very fine or use food processor.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Bake in greased dish at 375 for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: seafood salad(serves 10)
directions: Pour the ingredients in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Add over top a package Pepperidge herb stuffing mixture, then pour 1/2 cup melted butter over stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 325°.

title: hershey's deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan (two 9-inch or 13 x 9 x 2).
Stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt in mixing bowl.
Add eggs (which are at room temperature), milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Mix in the boiling water or hot coffee (I prefer coffee).
Batter will be thin.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes
for round pans or 35 to 40 minutes for rectangular pan.
Check with toothpick.
Cool and frost.
Great with peanut butter cooked icing.

title: low-fat cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage up in small parts.
Bring water to a boil with bouillon cubes and pepper.
Add cabbage; cover with lid and let simmer for 10 minutes on medium heat.

title: sugar-free rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix rhubarb, water, cinnamon, 1/4 cup flour and 24 packages Equal.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup flour, oatmeal, 24 packages Equal and oleo.
Put this topping on top of the rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Melt butter for later.
Combine Crisco in boiling water; add sugar and salt and let cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Beat in egg; add to first mixture and flour.
Mix well.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Knead and roll on floured board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in various sizes.
Dip one piece at a time in melted butter and drop around in Bundt pan.
Let set for 1 hour, then bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add flour and blend well.
Add milk slowly.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add corn and sugar.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese spinach bake
directions: Combine spinach, cottage cheese and nutmeg.
Fold stiffly beaten egg whites through the spinach mixture.
Pour into a nonstick baking dish or use pie plate sprayed with Pam.
Top with diced Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until firm).

title: april's spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef in large pot.
Drain off fat.
Add seasoning mix and tomatoes.
Cook for approximately 30 minutes.
Add Ragu sauce and heat thoroughly.
Serve over noodles.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onion and garlic.
Add salsa and pepper. Simmer 10 minutes.
Tear tortillas into bite size pieces.
In buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer half of the tortillas, half of the meat and half of the cheese; repeat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish rim with chopped tomatoes and 3 dollops of sour cream down the center.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Cook onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon shortening until tender. Add catsup and remaining ingredients.
Turn into 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, syrup and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in melted butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pastry shells.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes, or until firm.
Makes 3 regular pies.

title: spaghetti squash with meat sauce(microwave)
directions: Cook ground beef 3 to 4 minutes in a 2-quart casserole on full power. Drain fat. Add onion, carrots, celery and garlic; combine well. Cover and cook 8 minutes longer or until vegetables are soft; stir several times while cooking. Add remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese and squash. Cook, covered, on full power 5 minutes, then at half power 15
minutes. If sauce is too thick, add additional water.

title: 5 minute cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter at 350°.
In a large mixing bowl mix sugar, milk and baking powder.
Pour mixture over hot melted butter.
Place canned fruit of any kind evenly over batter. Pour juice over all.
Then sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar over that. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let sit 15 minutes.
Serve topped with ice cream or whipped cream. (Personally I like pears used with this best.)

title: nut bread
directions: Stir sugar and chopped nuts into Master Mix.
Combine milk and beaten egg; add to mix and blend well.
Bake in greased loaf pan in a moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour.
Yields 4 x 6-inch loaf.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Mix ingredients like regular pie dough.
Then add milk and egg and mix.

title: neiman-marcus bars
directions: Mix and press mixture of cake mix, butter and egg into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Then mix together powdered sugar, butter, eggs and cream cheese until creamy.
Pour over cake mix.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: hot chicken mix
directions: Combine ingredients.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese and 3/4 cup potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: white lasagne
directions: In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Saute mushrooms until lightly browned. Add wine and tarragon and cook over medium heat until juices have evaporated.
Set aside.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Cut bell peppers in strips.
Season ground beef with salt and ginger.
Make approximately 16 small balls.
Combine egg and water. I dip each ball into mixture and then roll in flour.
Saute in hot oil in large frypan (brown).
Add brown sugar, cornstarch or flour, vinegar and soy sauce.
Heat, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Boil 3 minutes and add meatballs, peppers and pineapple in syrup.
Cover and simmer approximately 30 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour, 7-Up and extract.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pop's spanish rice
directions: Saute pepper and onion until tender.
Add beef; cook.
Add tomato sauce and chili powder.
(Needs to be extra spicy; rice will absorb hot taste.)
Add rice and 1 to 1 1/2 cups water. Stir.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes over low heat.
Stir occasionally.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles; save juice.
Cut pickles lengthwise in quarters, then in half (8 pieces each pickle).
Put back in jar; layer with peppers and garlic.
Dissolve sugar in pickle juice (save 1/2 cup of juice; don't use).
Pour rest over pickles.
Set at room temperature for 24 hours, then put in fridge.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in small amount slightly salted water, about 15 minutes.
Add green pepper, cover and cook 3 minutes more.
Drain pineapple; save juice.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; stir in reserved juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in vegetables and pineapple; heat thoroughly.

title: cherry pie cake or 1, 2, 3 cake
directions: Grease an 8 x 10-inch square cake pan.
Put in cherry pie filling first.
Next, cake mix, then melted margarine.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocoladamias
directions: In a small, heavy saucepan, heat margarine or butter and half of white baking bar or pieces over low heat, just until melted, stirring occasionally (mixture will separate).
Meanwhile, coarsely chop remaining white baking bar or pieces; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat with an electric mixer until foamy.
Add sugar, then beat on high speed for 1 minute, until light.
Add margarine mixture, flour, vanilla and baking powder.
Beat until thoroughly combined, scraping sides of bowl often.
Stir in nuts and remaining chopped white baking bar or pieces.

title: pecan bars
directions: Beat eggs and stir in sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased 8-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool on board.
Cut into squares.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 360° for 45 minutes in greased pan.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well. Add the flour. Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Put in a 450° oven until golden brown.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Fill large cooking pot at least 1/2 full.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix together all other ingredients except macaroni and potatoes.
Cook around 30 minutes then add macaroni and potatoes. Serve when potatoes are tender.

title: bottom of the bag pie
directions: Take 1/4 cup of cereal powder crumbs; set aside.
Mix remaining crumbs and butter to make crust for pie.
Pat mixture into bottom of greased pie pan.
Then add pie filling on top; spread evenly. Sprinkle the 1/4 cup cereal crumbs on top.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
